title: best chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate pieces in top of a double boiler. Add butter and vanilla. Dip strawberries in chocolate, swirling to coat evenly. Place on wax paper and set in cool dry place. Make about 1 1/3 cups dip.

title: birdfeed
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight container.
Great to munch and healthy for kids.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Crumble one tube of crackers.
Place crumbs in lightly greased casserole dish.
Melt one stick of margarine in a bowl.
Combine melted margarine, beans, corn, water chestnuts, sour cream, soup and onion.
Pour mixture over cracker crumbs.
Crumble remaining tube of crackers and sprinkle crumbs over top of casserole.
Dot with remaining 1/2 stick of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
This makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry pork chops.
Lay in casserole dish.
Slice onion on chops. Slice layer of potatoes on onion.
Mix soup and can of water. Pour over layers and top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook the chicken; bone and skin and cut up into chunks. Combine the broth and soup and heat to a boil.
Pour over the chicken in a casserole or baking pan.
Mix the flour, melted margarine, buttermilk, salt and pepper and pour atop the chicken mixture.
Bake at 400° until crust is golden brown.

title: chili-mac(quick and easy)
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes, salt, chili powder, sugar, vinegar and water and stir all into meat mixture. Bring to a boil and add dry macaroni.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: cappuccino cooler
directions: In a blender container, place all ingredients except whipped cream.
Cover; blend until smoothed.
Serve immediately over crushed ice.
Garnish with whipped cream.
Makes about four 6 ounce servings.

title: applequed pork chops
directions: Brown steak in shortening and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cook onion in skillet until tender.
Place onion on top of steaks. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over steaks.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: unique chocolate sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa and blend.
Add sugar.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is almost melted.
Add milk slowly and blend.
Bring to a full, rolling boil and cook 2 to 2 1/2 minutes. Cool.
Add vanilla.

title: strawberry snowcake
directions: Tear cake into pieces.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Whip cream cheese, Cool Whip and milk together; pour over cake.
Toss lightly.
Put into refrigerator and chill.

title: hungarian macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, mushrooms with juice and pimentos and juice.
Toss macaroni with onion, pepper, mushroom and pimentos.
Arrange in 2 layers.
Macaroni, cheese and sauce.
Top with crumbs and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: oriental salad
directions: Dry Mix: In a medium bowl, add broccoli and cole slaw mix, Ramen noodles broken apart, chopped up green onions, sunflower seeds and almonds.

title: old-fashioned baked ham
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Place ham in a baking pan on a rack.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Drain cubed cheese.
Add tomatoes and hot sauce.
Put all into crock-pot. Great to use with chips.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form meat balls and bake at 400° for 12 mins. or until brown.

title: marinated shrimp dip
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and mustard well, then add onions, celery and shrimp.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on crackers.

title: chicken delight(serves 6)
directions: Combine Home Style vegetables, including liquid, cooked diced chicken, soup, cheese and 1 teaspoon celery seed in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with biscuits and sprinkle remaining celery seed on top.
Return to oven.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes until biscuits are brown.

title: au gratin casserole
directions: Combine ingredients, except oleo, and mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook for approximately 1 hour.
After removing from oven, melt oleo and pour over top.
Let soak.
Serve.

title: italian meatballs
directions: This is an old Italian receipt that has no exact measurements. Just mix until it is a nice consistency.

title: sausage dip
directions: Cook sausage in pan, breaking it up with fork as it cooks. Drain. (This can be done ahead and frozen in a Ziploc bag. Then when you need it you can defrost and add other ingredients.)

title: grandma's fruit cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add applesauce; add fruit, raisins, currants and nuts, mixing well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and spices, sifting together as you add to
the applesauce mixture.
The batter will be quite stiff.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 1 hour. Put a pan of water under it in oven.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.
Let cool in pan for about 5 minutes.
Turn out of pan and continue to cool.
When thoroughly cool, wrap in Saran Wrap and then in aluminum foil.
Put away in a cool place to season. Should be about a month before you want to use it.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Mix eggs and Ricotta.

Set aside. Brown meats and drain. Add taco seasoning, onions and tomatoes. Cook for 10 minutes. Add chilli. Layer in a 9 x 12 baking dish 1/2 meat mixture, 2 tortillas, Ricotta and egg mixture and 1/2 the shredded cheese. Make two layers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let stand a few minutes before cutting. It freezes well.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning, sour cream and mayonnaise together and let stand in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Pour mixture into large serving dish; spread evenly.
Top with one layer shredded lettuce, one layer chopped tomatoes, one layer shredded cheese and one layer sliced black olives.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Stir in flour, sugar, nuts, baking soda, salt and eggs.
Heat oven to 300°.
Shape into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy; add sugar, oil, vanilla, rhubarb and nuts.
Sift together dry ingredients and mix with creamed mixture.
Bake in two loaf pans for 50 minutes at 350°. Chill 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and mix well.
Then blend all dry ingredients into liquid ingredients.
Stir in blueberries and orange marmalade.

title: pastor sallie's peanut butter chocolate chip ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, salt, flour, half and half, vanilla, peanut butter and up to 4 quarts milk in ice cream freezer.
Freeze. Add chocolate chips after ice cream begins freezing.
(We always make this on July 4th.)

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Combine eggs and jam; mix well.
Add to creamed mixture; beat well.
Combine buttermilk and soda; set aside.
Combine dry ingredients; mix alternately with creamed mixture and buttermilk mixture.
Mix well. Stir in raisins and pecans.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda; add them to first bowl.
Add the chocolate chips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter together.
Press in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Mix cream cheese, 2 cups sugar and enough milk to thin to spreading consistency.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Layer bananas and crushed pineapple. Top with Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together and cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
For meringue, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar; brown.

title: classic squash casserole
directions: Cook squash about 5 minutes.
Drain.
Combine squash, onion, green pepper and rice.
Blend eggs, soup, milk and mayonnaise. Stir into squash mixture.
Stir in part of cheese but reserve some and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: biscuit mix
directions: May add 9 cups of sugar for scones.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken-n-rice
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in baking pan (9 x 12-inch). Sprinkle the dry onion soup in rice mixture.
Lay chicken on top. Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours for chicken with bone or 1 hour for boneless chicken.

title: easy pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops; drain and add sauerkraut, mushrooms and soup.
Simmer on low until pork chops are done.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: baked salmon cakes
directions: In large bowl, break salmon into small chunks with a fork. Remove skin if desired.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Spoon into muffin pans.
It will make 12 muffins.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top of each muffin.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Saute celery and green peppers in butter like for stir-fry. Don't overcook, as it needs to be crisp.
Add rest of ingredients. Heat until bubbly.
Serve over rice.
Portions freeze well.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Cut stem end of each pepper and cut in half lengthwise.
Wash outside and inside.
Remove all seeds and membranes.
Cook peppers in boiling salted water 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Stuff each half pepper lightly with mixture.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: banana  bread(low fat version)
directions: Measure and sift together flour, baking soda, and salt. Cream butter, add sugar. Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs and vanilla. Stir until thoroughly mixed. Stir in mashed bananas. Fold in dry ingredients. Spray 2 small loaf pans with Pam. Pour in mixture. Bake at 325° for 55-60 minutes.

title: garlic mustard
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on speed (3) until garlic is blended with mustard.
Serve with most hot meats. It can be used on sandwiches and also as a sauce.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into a buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese in medium bowl until smooth and fluffy; beat in 1/2 cup sugar and the eggs.
Stir in 2/3 cup of pineapple juice.
Pour cream cheese mixture into a large graham cracker crust.
Bake just until the center is set, about 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: spanish corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Cook 45 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Press crushed pretzel sticks, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes and cool.
Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar. Stir in the whipped topping.
Blend and place on the pretzel crust.
Combine strawberry gelatin, frozen strawberries and boiling water.
Let cool slightly.
Spoon onto the cream cheese layer and refrigerate.

title: strawberries and cream cake
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and water.
Beat in pudding mix. Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: cheese roll-ups
directions: Blend all ingredients to a spreading consistency.
Spread over large tortilla and roll like a jelly roll.
Refrigerate overnight and slice into 1-inch serving pieces.
Serve on tray with bowl of extra picante sauce for dipping.
Can be made several days ahead.
Makes enough to do all tortillas in package.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat; spoon off (drain) excess fat.
Place Doritos in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread ground beef evenly over chips.
Place chopped onions over ground beef.

title: brenda's texas barbecue brisket
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over brisket and let marinate overnight.
Fresh onion and celery can be added before baking. Remove celery, but bake in marinade.
Bake at 250° for approximately 5 hours.
Drain liquids.
Pour on 8 ounces of your favorite barbecue sauce on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour. Slice thin and serve on rolls.

title: harvard beets
directions: Canned beets or fresh beets may be used.
In a saucepan, mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in vinegar.
Allow to boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly to make a thick, smooth sauce.
Add cooked beets, diced or sliced, and allow the mixture to stand on warm heat for 1/2 hour to blend flavors.
Just before serving, add butter.
Reheat and serve warm.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugars.
Beat well.
Add everything else and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butter pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in large bowl; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in enough water with a fork, just until flour is moistened.

title: beets in orange sauce
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
In saucepan, stir beet liquid with cornstarch to make smooth paste.
Add marmalade, vinegar and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add margarine, then add beets and stir gently over low heat until evenly glazed and heated through.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed bacon rolls
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in stuffing mix.
Remove from heat.
Add liquid and mix thoroughly.
Wrap 1 full teaspoon in 1/2 strip bacon.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° until bacon cooks.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix. Make tiny balls.
Bake 15 minutes, covered.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.
Makes about 30.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixer bowl until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for about 45 minutes.
This is a very moist, delicious cake.

title: brunswick stew
directions: That is it. Put it all together and heat on stove or in crock-pot.

title: chicken breasts with orange sauce
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with 1/4 teaspoon of the salt (if desired).
Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Add chicken; brown both sides.
Remove from skillet.
Add flour, sugar, mustard, cinnamon, ginger and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt to drippings in pan.
Stir to a smooth paste.
Gradually add orange juice mixed with chicken broth; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Add chicken breasts.
Cover; simmer over low heat until chicken is tender, about 25 to 30 minutes.
If you wish, 3 cups of hot, cooked rice may be served with the chicken.
May be done ahead.
Reheats well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: egg nog
directions: Combine well beaten eggs, Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and salt until blended.
Gradually beat in milk; fold in whipped cream. Pour into punch bowl or serving cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon to taste.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: caramel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat sugar, butter and milk in cake pan until boiling.
Spread pecans over syrup and add biscuits.
Place pan in oven and cook until biscuits are done, about 10 minutes. Remove from oven and flip onto plate.
Serve while hot.

title: crunchy broiled fish
directions: Preheat broiler.
In one bowl, mix together mustard, yogurt and Tabasco.
In another bowl, bread or cracker crumbs, dried onions and Italian seasoning.
Dip fillets in yogurt mixture, then crumb mixture.
Place on broiler pan that has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Broil 5 minutes; turn fish over and broil an additional 3 to 5 minutes or until fish is no longer translucent.

title: lemon angel food cake dessert
directions: Slice angel food cake into 3 layers.
Combine yogurt and pie filling until creamy.
Spread onto angel food cake in layers.
Top with Cool Whip and fruit.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Save the grease and in that cook until tender the celery, green pepper and onion.
In large bowl, put rice and soup mix.
Add hot water.
Add celery and meat mixture and chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer and beat at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand in pan 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad log
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt, ginger, pepper and pepper sauce.
Stir in chicken, eggs and 1/4 cup green onions.
Shape into log, 8 x 2-inches.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.
Cut bell pepper rings to make strips.
Place strips diagonally across log; divide log into 4 sections.
Sprinkle sesame seed on one section.
Repeat with 3 tablespoons onion, the olives and the pimento on remaining sections.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spread the rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Lay chicken pieces on top of rice.
Mix the soup and water together.
Pour gently over top of chicken and rice.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours at about 350°.

title: white christmas fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in heavy saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches boil.
Cook to 234°.
Remove from heat and cool to 110°, about 1 hour.
Add vanilla and beat until it holds its shape (or until it begins to lose its gloss).
Stir in walnuts and cherries; pour into buttered pan.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: orange jello surprise
directions: Mix jello, pudding and water; bring to boil.
Let boil until starts to thicken.
Then let cool and add oranges and Cool Whip.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in pan over low heat; add brown sugar and cook until foamy.
Stir in boiling water and remove from heat.
Mix cornstarch, flour and salt; stir into milk and then add to brown sugar syrup and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in a little egg yolks, then mix all together and cook 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and cool.
Put in pie crust.
Add meringue.

title: crispy oat cookies
directions: Cream the butter; gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed.
Add egg and beat well.
Add oil and vanilla, mixing well. Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheets, flattening each ball with the tines of a fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly. Remove from cookie sheets and cool on wire racks.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown beef; pour off excess fat.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Chop onions and part of tops finely.
Mix with softened cream cheese and sour cream.
Grease a baking dish lightly.
Put layers of noodles, meat sauce, sour cream mixture and grated cheese on top of casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Can be mixed the day before and is really good.
Serves 8.

title: black magic cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add all dry ingredients and stir.
Add liquids while stirring.
Batter will be runny.
Cooking time:
30 to 35 minutes.
Temperature:
Pan size:
9 x 13-inches.

title: butter supreme pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together. Add flour, 7-Up and extract.
Mix well. Beat eggs slightly. Add to mixture; beat well. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Glaze lightly while warm.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Place egg whites in bowl.
Beat with spoon until slightly frothy.
Add oil and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in sugar and cocoa.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Oil bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 26 to 28 minutes.
Avoid overbaking.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Cover with the other pie shell, crimp edges, trim and slash top 3 or 4 times. Bake at 350°
for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Serve.

title: crescent squares
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Bake crescent rolls flat on cookie sheet at 325° until golden brown. Cool.
Spread cream cheese all over top of crescent roll.
Top with strawberries, oranges or other fruits.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add meat, milk, onion, parsley, crackers and salt and pepper.
With hands, mix thoroughly.
Form into 2 loaves in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add catsup on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: chocolate layer bars
directions: Combine chocolate chips, cream cheese and evaporated milk in medium pan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Blend well and set aside.

title: microwave ham roll-ups
directions: Never put metal or aluminum foil in the microwave oven.
Place Tater Tots in microwave oven on paper plate or towel.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes or until thawed. Place 1 cheese slice on each ham slices.
Spread each cheese slice with small amount of sour cream.
Place 3 Tater Tots inside each ham-cheese slice. Roll up and fasten with a toothpick.
Place on serving platter. Microwave on High for 2 1/2 minutes or until hot.

title: french farmhouse garlic chicken
directions: Rinse chicken, pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper.
In a 10 inch skillet, heat oil over medium high heat.
Add chicken and garlic cloves.
Cook chicken for 2 to 3 minutes on each side or just till brown, turning once.
Slowly add 1/2 cup wine or broth, the second cup 1/2 cup broth, lemon juice, basil and oregano. Cover and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes or till chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer chicken and garlic to warm platter; keep warm.
In a small bowl, stir together flour and the 2 tablespoons wine or broth.
Stir into pan juices. Boil.
Cook and stir for 1 minute more.
Spoon over chicken and serve with potatoes, rice and zucchini.

title: becky's hamburger and bean casserole
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces.
Add chopped onion and saute until onion is done.
Add hamburger and cook until no pink left in meat. Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch oven dish and bake at 375°
for 45 minutes.
Serves 6. Bake for 1 hour for drier beans.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Using very hot tap water, prepare lasagna noodles as label directs; drain.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in a baking dish.
Top with mixture of the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° until apples are done.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Put self-rising flour in large bowl.
Put hole in flour.
Work in all ingredients.
Make 4 or 5 layers.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Put dried apples between layers.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Combine drained spinach with the Ricotta cheese. Layer ingredients in 9 x 12-inch pan in the following order: Spinach and Ricotta mixture, spaghetti sauce, noodles and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat until ingredients are used up, ending top 2 layers with sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Makes 12 servings. Each serving contains 261 calories and 6.9 g fat.

title: struedel cake
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Add sour cream.
Divide into 2 or 3 parts. Refrigerate 3 or 4 hours.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick. Spread with apricot jam.
Mix raisins and walnuts together. Spread thinly on top of jam.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Roll as for jelly roll.
Cut slits in top 1/2-inch apart. Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: chocolate-orange mousse
directions: In a small bowl, combine topping mix and 1/2 cup of the milk. Beat with electric mixer on high for 2 minutes (until mixture forms stiff peaks).
Add remaining milk, orange juice and pudding mix. Beat with electric mixer on low just until mixed.
Beat on medium about 2 minutes or until well mixed.
Fold in chocolate pieces. Spoon mixture into 6 dessert dishes.
Quick chill in freezer for 20 minutes or so before serving.
If desired, garnish with orange curls.
Serves 6. Contains 116 calories and 4 grams fat per serving.

title: chopped salad
directions: Chop up both heads of lettuce; add package of cabbage, green onions, raisins and toasted sesame seed in skillet on medium for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add to lettuce.
Also add mushrooms.
Pour dressing; toss well and serve.
Serves 4.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat 1 egg with fork.
Add 1 cup white sugar and 1 cup peanut butter.
Mix well.
Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sally's spinach salad dressing
directions: Whip with a fork until desired consistency.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Beat brown sugar and butter until fluffy.
Stir in Bisquick and nuts until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining mixture in pan.
Bake 12 minutes.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Combine both mixtures.
Divide and pour into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie crusts.
Bake 60 minutes.
Bake at 400° first 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° next 45 minutes.
Stick with silver knife. When it comes out clean, it is done.

title: lemon cream dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans; pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°; allow to cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and most of Cool Whip (reserve enough to cover top of dessert).
Spread over cooled crust.
Beat milk and pudding mix until smooth and thick.
Pour over cream cheese layer and top with rest of Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: nut and date squares
directions: Beat eggs; add everything, except dates and nuts.
Mix well, then add cut up dates and nuts.
Do not chop in blender.
Spread in 8-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, then at 300° for 15 minutes.
Toothpick should be a little sticky.
Do not overbake.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: my favorite meat loaf
directions: Cut bread into small pieces.
Pour milk over bread; let stand while mixing the rest of the ingredients, mixing very good.
This is very important.
After completely mixing meat mixture, pour bread mixture into meat mixture and mix until you see no more bread.
The mixture will tighten up as you mix.
Put into a loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: betty's spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake for about 20 to 25 minutes, until bubbly. Add reserved cheese and return to oven for 5 to 10 more minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: babe's apple cake
directions: Stir together flour, wheat germ, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg; set aside.
In large bowl, combine sugars, apples, oil, walnuts, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; stir gently with wooden spoon.
Blend well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool in pan on rack.
Sprinkle with sifted confectioners sugar.
Cut into 12 pieces.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients in order, stirring only to moisten.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and broth and pour over chicken.
Mix flour, margarine and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: potato soup
directions: In stainless steel pot, bring water and potatoes to a boil. Cook until tender; drain. Cook onions, celery and chicken base in a second pot with same amount of water until al dente. After draining potatoes, put in pot with vegetables. Add half and half. Add roux and heat until soup thickens.

title: chicken corn casserole
directions: Dice
chicken,
use all ingredients mixed well together. Cook in casserole dish 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: mushroom nut pate
directions: Steam mushrooms, onions and garlic in 3 tablespoons water. Remove from heat, drain and reserve the liquid.

title: conrad's favorite omelet
directions: If you like it hot and are brave, try jalapeno peppers!

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Warm milk, add yeast, sugar, and butter.
Then add flour mix. Knead on floured board.
Spread out on melted butter (wax paper). Fold.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Then cut into biscuits.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cheddar chicken
directions: Cut the chicken into bite-size pieces and saute in oil until the chicken turns white.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towel.
Cook broccoli or asparagus.
In mixing bowl, blend soup, mayo, lemon juice and curry powder.
In bottom of loaf pan, place broccoli or asparagus on top of vegetables.
Arrange chicken to cover vegetables and chicken.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Bake in 350° oven for about 35 minutes or until the cheese is completely melted.

title: trimmed-down macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, omitting salt and fat.
Drain well and set aside.
Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in salt and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Gradually stir about 1/4 of hot mixture into egg substitute.
Add remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Stir cheese sauce into macaroni and pour into a 2-quart baking dish coated with cooking spray. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 5 1/2 cups.
Contains 160 calories per 1/2 cup serving.

title: cheese torte
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch baking dish with graham cracker crumbs, buttered.
Melt marshmallows with 1/2 cup milk; cool.
Whip cream cheese.
Add to cooled mixture.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pan.
Cool at least for 5 hours or overnight.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine ingredients. Chill several hours. Serve cold.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift the flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder together. Cream together the butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add the 2 eggs, rolled oats, vanilla and chocolate chips and mix well.
Stir in the sifted dry ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: best ever muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Make a well in center. Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients. Stir quickly just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Put any kind of fruit or jelly you like in them, 1 cup fruit (blueberries) or 1 teaspoon of jelly per muffin.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: diabetic banana pecan frozen dessert
directions: Allow frozen ice cream to thaw slightly.
Beat in mashed banana and chopped pecans.
Pack in a freezer container.
Cover and freeze until firm.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a Dutch oven. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove cloves and chill.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat egg slowly.
Add oil and vanilla, then sugar.
Measure out flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Add to wet ingredients. Finish by adding nuts, raisins and apples.
Batter should be quite stiff.
Put in floured and greased 7 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Fry chicken wings until golden brown.
Melt butter and add butter to hot sauce.
Take large bowl and add chicken wings and sauce; mix well.
Re-fry chicken wings for 2 minutes.
Add back to sauce and top with Blue cheese dressing and celery.

title: baked tortilla chips
directions: Brush each tortilla lightly with oil on one side.
Stack and cut into eighths.
Place tortilla chips on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until crisp and light brown, about 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings of 8 chips.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and heat until thickened.
Add jello and cool.
Put fruit in pie shell and pour liquid mixture over fruit.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine cake mix and margarine in bowl until crumbly.
Combine Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter in second bowl (easier to mix if slightly warmed in microwave).
Reserve 1 1/2 cups cake mixture.
Pat remaining into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with marshmallow/pecan mix.
Crumble cake mix over that.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Underbaking is acceptable.

title: stew beef with vegetables
directions: Cook stew beef in water, garlic, tomatoes, onion and tomato sauce until tender.
Add potatoes, carrots and celery.
Cook until done.
Cook egg noodles as directed on package.
Drain noodles and serve stew beef on top of noodles.
Serves 6.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Beat first 10 ingredients at low speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Frost with favorite frosting.

title: lentil soup
directions: In a medium, non-reactive casserole, heat the oil over moderate heat.
Add the onion, celery, carrots, garlic, thyme and bay leaf. Cover and cook until the onion is translucent, about 5 minutes. Add the wine and bring to a boil over high heat.
Add the tomatoes with their juice, breaking them up with the back of a spoon.
Add the lentils and chicken broth and return to a boil.
Reduce the heat to moderately low; cover partially and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the lentils are tender, about 35 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper and serve hot.

title: pork chop supreme
directions: Place raw pork chops in shallow baking dish.
Add a lemon and onion slice, 1 teaspoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon catsup to each chop.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, depending on thickness of chops.
Can substitute ReaLemon for lemon slices.

title: creamy lettuce salad
directions: Cut one egg into wedges for garnish.
Dice remaining eggs. In a salad bowl combine the greens, tomatoes, onion and diced eggs. After mixing dressing pour over salad and toss to coat.
Garnish with egg wedges.
Serve immediately.

title: shelter harbor coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube or Bundt pan. Cream butter and 2 cups sugar.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt in a separate bowl.
Fold dry ingredients into the wet mixture.
Beat until just blended (do not overbeat).
In another bowl, add 3/4 cup sugar, pecans, nutmeg and cinnamon.

title: ham burgundy with onion rice
directions: In a large pot, combine cranberry sauce, cranberry juice, mustard, salt and pepper and cloves.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in ham and heat thoroughly.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Pour over cooked rice.
Serve ham mixture over onion rice.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sprinkle 1 cup pecans in each pie shell.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can add more pecans, if you desire.

title: oakley's bread and butter pickles
directions: Day One:
Use 1 cup of salt to 1 gallon of water.
Wash cucumbers and leave whole.
Pour salt water over and let set for 1 day (24 hours).

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet (5 minutes each side).
Slice potatoes and lay in greased casserole pan.
Remove pork chops from skillet.
Butter skillet, add soup, milk and cheese and simmer until cheese melts and mixture thickens.
Pour mixture over potatoes (mix in well).
Lay pork chops on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil, bake 10 minutes more.

title: prune cake with glaze
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl; mix well.
Pour into a large baking dish which has been greased and lightly floured. Bake at 325° until done, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in a little water on top of stove for not more than 3 or 4 minutes.
Turn off heat and let sit there with lid on while you mix remaining ingredients.
Line a large, flat pan with herb stuffing mix after buttering, then pour squash mixture in. Top with rest of herb stuffing mix.
Dot with butter all over and bake until brown.

title: chicken noodle pilaf
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in oleo.
Remove chicken; stir in water, rice and soup mix.
Add chicken and cover.
Simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: smothered burritos
directions: Brown hamburger, and season with diced onions, salt and pepper.
Drain and place first four ingredients in a bowl and stir.
Place 2 big spoonfuls of mixed ingredients in a flour burrito and roll.
Place in 9 X 13 inch pan sprayed with Pam. Open green chili can or use your own to top the burritos.
Spread out so all burritos are covered.
Place 2 cups shredded cheese on top and place in oven for 30 minutes at 350° or place in a glass 9 X 13 inch pan and place in microwave until cheese melts about 20 minutes.
I make this for all volleyball or basketball dinners. The girls love it.
It is easy to make ahead and place in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Dice all vegetables.
Set aside.
Cook spaghetti as usual (break into 3 to 4 inch pieces).
Rinse, drain and pour a small amount of cooking oil over spaghetti (tablespoon or so) to keep from sticking and put in refrigerator to cool.

title: marzetti
directions: Brown meat and add onions, green peppers and celery (cut fine). Add tomatoes and mushrooms.
Cook noodles.
Mix all together in casserole.
Cover top with grated "nippy" cheese.
Bake 1 hour. Remove lid last 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all in the order given.
Bake in 350° oven on middle rack 35 to 40 minutes in 12 x 8-inch or 2 (9-inch) round pans.

title: easy bake round steak
directions: Tenderize steak. Put large piece of foil on rectangular pan. Place steak on foil and dab margarine all over. Drain mushrooms and spread over steak. Sprinkle with soup mix and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: white chocolate pecans
directions: Melt a little butter in a pan.
Lay pecans in pan and toast. Pour into melted white chocolate.
Mix and put on waxed paper with a spoon.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Saute onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Place 1/2 of potatoes into a lightly greased 5-quart rectangular roaster.
Prepare a white sauce by melting 1/2 cup margarine.
Add flour, cornstarch, pepper and salt; stir until heated.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add sauteed onion and green pepper to white sauce.
Pour half the sauce over sliced potatoes.
Add 1/2 of grated cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until potatoes are done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, oats and margarine until crumbly. Place apples in 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Cover with crumb mix.
Cook other ingredients until thick and clear; pour over crumbs.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.
Use with other fruit:
cherries, rhubarb and peaches.

title: baked chicken
directions: Take skin off chicken.
Spray dish with Pam.
Sprinkle chicken with onion powder, salt, if desired, and pepper to taste.
Place in baking dish.
Add onion and celery.
Mix gravy mix with water and pour around chicken.
Cover and bake.

title: taquito bake
directions: Layer taquitos in baking dish.
Top with Ranch beans, enchilada sauce and grated cheese.
Bake at 325 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: quick egg white frosting
directions: Heat syrup to a boil.
Beat eggs and salt for 30 seconds until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, continuing to beat until stiff peaks form, about 1 minute.
Slowly add boiling corn syrup to egg white mixture.
Add vanilla.
Continue beating until frosting becomes thick enough to spread, about 3 minutes.
Makes large amount.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells as directed on box.
Drain and cool a little bit for easier handling.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain fat. Cook dressing according to package directions.
Combine ground beef with dressing in large bowl.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with Pam.
Pour enough spaghetti sauce over bottom of casserole to cover.
Fill each shell with dressing and hamburg mixture.
Then top with shredded cheese and place in casserole. After all shells have been filled, pour spaghetti sauce over them. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove aluminum foil after first 45 minutes of baking time.

title: potato burger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine meat, bread crumbs, egg, catsup, beef bouillon and pepper.
Press on bottom and side to rim of 9-inch pie plate.
Combine potatoes, onion, mushrooms and 1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon over meat.
Cover, bake for 45 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Top with remaining 1 1/2 cups cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer or until melted.
Serves 6.

title: holiday pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Place wax paper on cookie sheet and put pretzels flat on wax paper.
Place a Hershey Hug inside each pretzel ring.
Put in oven for 5 minutes (chocolate will still look hard, but any longer will make them too soft).
Take out and immediately place one M&M candy piece on Hershey Hug.
Gently push down on M&M just until chocolate fills the entire pretzel. Chocolate Hug will flatten and harden within the pretzel ring. Let harden for a few hours and remove from wax paper.
Enjoy!!

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown hamburg, drain fat and add remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour or more.
Enjoy!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place uncooked rolls in bottom of ungreased 11 x 13-inch pan. Beat eggs; pour over crescent rolls.
Fry sausage.
Drain sausage; sprinkle over eggs.
Sprinkle grated cheese over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mixture may be fixed the night before, left in the fridge and baked the next morning.

title: brandied fruit cake
directions: Stir each day for 10 days.
Add 2 1/2 cups sugar and 1 large can crushed pineapple and juice.
Stir each day for 10 days.
On 20th day, add two 10 ounce jars of maraschino cherries, chopped and drained (no juice).
Stir each day for 10 days.
On 30th day, drain well.
Save juice for starter.
Fruit makes 3 cakes.

title: three bean dish
directions: Cook onion in bacon grease.
Mix all ingredients and add onion.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in salted boiling water about 8 minutes.
Drain. Melt butter in baking dish.
Put layer of cooked eggplant in dish.
Add layer of celery, bread crumbs and cheese, saving 1/4 cup cheese for top.
Combine egg and milk; pour over mixture. Cover top with bread crumbs and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until well browned.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add sour cream, vanilla, flour, baking powder, and baking soda.
Spread 1/2 batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle 1/2 of chocolate chips over batter.
Spread batter and top with sugar mix; add chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheeses, dressing and olives.
Lightly grease a mini (or regular) muffin tin and press one wrapper in each cup. Lightly spray with Pam.
Bake 5 minutes, until golden brown. Remove from tins; place on a baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: double chocolate chewies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine dry cake mix, oil and eggs in bowl; mix well (mixture will be stiff). Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts, using your hands if necessary. Pat mixture into even layer in pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool in pan on rack.
Cut into bars.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Place peanut butter and marshmallow cream in large bowl; set aside.
Combine sugar, milk, margarine and vanilla; cook for 1 1/2 minutes on medium heat (rolling boil).
Pour over peanut butter and marshmallow cream; mix until smooth.
Pour into pan.

title: walnut acorn cookies
directions: Stir together butter, brown sugar, 3/4 cup walnuts and vanilla. Sift flour with baking powder and stir into butter mixture.
Blend well.
Shape cookies by pressing dough lightly into teaspoon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for about 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: grits and cheese casserole
directions: Cook grits in boiling water until soupy, add salt.
Cut cream cheese in small pieces.
Stir into grits and add margarine.
While cheese and margarine melt, break eggs in cup.
Fill cup with milk. Heat together and add to grits.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 300 degrees for 45 minutes, then sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Bake 10 minutes longer and serve hot.

title: instant spice tea mix
directions: Serve 2 to 3 tsp. in 1 cup of boiling water.

title: cream cheese tarts(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Mix in flour.
Form into a ball. Chill in freezer for 1 hour.
Break off small ball of dough and fit into greased mini tart pans.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet together with onions and pepper to taste, if desired.
Drain well.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix butter and cheese.
Add rest of ingredients.
Shape into marble size balls.
Place balls on cookie sheet lined with foil. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Flatten balls and serve.

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Drain juice off the fruit cocktail and pineapple chunks.
Add marshmallows, coconut, raisins and walnuts and add Cool Whip last. Chill in the refrigerator.

title: quick asparagus roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll bread, 1 slice at a time, until flat.
Spread with a thin layer of cheese.
Place 1 spear of asparagus at edge of each slice and "roll."
Slice into 3 bite-size pieces.
Brush with butter.
Bake until browned, turning once. Serve hot.

title: baked ravioli
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In skillet, cook beef until brown and crumbly.
Drain fat.
Stir in salt, egg, cheese, onion and crumbs. Prepare pie crusts according to package directions.
Cut dough into 3 pieces.
Roll out each piece of dough on a floured surface. Cut each in half.
On one half of each dough sheet arrange 12 tiny balls of meat.
Moisten the other half sheet and place over meat.
Cut into squares and seal each ravioli with fork.
Place side by side on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Heat spaghetti sauce and spoon over ravioli.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: With a fork, mix together first 4 ingredients.
In a separate dish, beat remaining ingredients.
Combine the 2 mixtures, stirring with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Mold dough with hands in a ball.
Chill for at least 30 minutes before using.
You can separate into balls of dough and freeze separately or roll into your favorite crust and fill or bake.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Very good!

title: chicken with milani's 1890 french dressing
directions: Bake chicken pieces at 350° until cooked.
Cook frozen peas until tender.
Boil potato pieces until cooked; do not overcook. After the chicken is cooked, drain the grease from the pan and drain the water from the potatoes and peas.
Combine chicken, potatoes and peas.
Shake bottle of dressing well and add to chicken mixture.
Fill dressing bottle halfway with water and pour into 4 corners of the pan.
Put pan back into oven for 15 minutes.

title: garbanzo chicken style
directions: Blend garbanzos in bran water.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix.
Add mixture to garbanzos.
Blend at low speed to develop gluten.
Pour into sprayed flat baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with your favorite seasoning.
Place chicken (skin side up) in crock-pot.
Sprinkle paprika over chicken; add no water.
Cook on high for about 30 minutes, then turn it on medium until chicken is done, about 2 to 3 hours.
Remember, always wash chicken before cooking.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown meat. Add tomato soup and spices.
Simmer 15 minutes. Cook noodles and drain. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Put half the noodles in bottom. Cover with 1/2 the sauce and 1/2 the cheese.
Repeat.
Sprinkle top with cheese. Cover pan with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and allow to brown for 15 more minutes.

title: lemon-pecan sticky rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, combine sugars, margarine, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Reserve 1/4 cup lemon mixture.
Pour remaining mixture into 9-inch round cake pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Separate rolls into 8 rectangles and spread with remaining mixture.
Roll up jelly roll fashion, beginning with short sides; seal edges.
Cut each roll in half.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour in pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green bean bake
directions: In a casserole dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper. Stir in green beans and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: oven baked tomatoes
directions: Put tomatoes in baking dish and salt and pepper.
Top each tomato well with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crisp sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla. Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients in fourths, beating after each addition.
Chill dough for 1 hour.

title: georgia powell's mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Empty mixed vegetables in a Pyrex bowl.
Mix cheese and mayonnaise with vegetables.
Crumble crackers and pour over melted butter.
Put buttered cracker crumbs over mixture of vegetables. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: kool aid cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, mixing well.
In separate bowl, mix flour, powder and salt.
Mix dry ingredients alternately with milk to first mixture.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375` for 12 minutes.
Makes approximately 40 cookies.
Cool.
Top with icing.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Into small bowl, measure flour, brown sugar, butter or margarine, vanilla, salt and egg yolk.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until blended, constantly scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Increase speed to medium; beat 1 minute.
With hands, shape dough in 3/4-inch balls.

title: spanish beefburger
directions: Combine beef, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, Tabasco sauce, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into one large patty.
Place on broiler pan; broil 3 inches from source of heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cut tomatoes in half; scoop 1 tablespoon pulp out of each half.
Mix pulp with cheese and green pepper.
Sprinkle each half with salt and pepper.
Stuff tomatoes lightly with cheese mixture.
Turn meat and place tomatoes on rack.
Broil 5 minutes. Cook onion rings in butter until brown.
Pour catsup over meat. Place onions on meat; continue broiling for 5 minutes.

title: toffee grahams
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Break graham crackers into sticks and lay flat side by side to cover pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine butter, margarine and sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes; remove from heat and add nuts.
Pour over crackers and bake for 10 minutes.
Cool and cut between crackers.

title: saucepan brownies(from snowdrift can in 1947)
directions: Melt together over hot water chocolate and Snowdrift.
Beat in sugar and eggs.
Sift together and stir in flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix in chopped nuts.
Spread in greased oblong pan (9 x 13-inch) and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with favorite chocolate icing.

title: corn and broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients but croutons.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cover with croutons and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 4.

title: kid's fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; stir gently to combine.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, slightly beat eggs.
Add pineapple including juice, sugar, flour, soda and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients well, then fold in nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: super secret ingredient cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg.
Beat well. Stir in the warm beans and liquid.
Stir in all the dry ingredients, raisins and add the apples. (The batter will be stiff.)

title: red cabbage salad
directions: Core cabbage and cut in half from top downward through stem end.
Shred or slice in very thin slices.
Place the cabbage in a large bowl and toss with grated carrot, diced celery and apple. In another bowl mix oil, vinegar, sugar and caraway seed.
Season liberally with salt and pepper.
Toss cabbage mixture and dressing, then serve immediately or refrigerate (covered tightly) up to 24 hours.
Yield:
8 servings.
Carbohydrate 15 g, protein 2 g, fat 10 g, calories 153.

title: almond snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beat until light and add flour, salt and almonds.
Add vanilla and mix with hands, dough should hold together.
Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Make round cookies in palm of your hands, place on foil lined ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 20 - 25 minutes or until cookies are light brown.
While still warm dust with confectioners sugar and allow to cool.
Yields about 60 cookies.

title: kona banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in banana.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to banana mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased 9x9x2 inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes. Serve with good coffee to good friends.

title: pretzel snack
directions: Break up pretzels into bite size pieces.
Mix with all of the ingredients and stir well.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.
Mix every 10 minutes.
Turn oven off and let them cool in oven.
Serve.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Spoon a heaping tablespoon of chicken mixture into each tortilla.
Roll.
Place seam side down in Pam sprayed 13 x 9-inch baking dish after all are rolled.
Spoon enchilada sauce over each roll completely.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes maximum. Serve with saffron rice, if desired.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter/oleo. Add eggs one at a time. Add all rest. Mix well (not beat). Grease a tube pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hershey brownies
directions: Beat together margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs one at a time.
Beat until well blended.
Add 1 can Hershey's syrup plus the flour.
Mix well.
Pour into jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until tooth pick comes out clean. Let cool completely and frost.

title: crock-pot hamburger casserole
directions: Put layers of vegetables in the order given in slow cooker. Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Put the lightly browned ground beef on top of the celery.
Mix tomato soup and can of water and pour over top of beef.
Cover and set on low for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 2 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally. Ingredients may be increased by half for a 5-quart model cooker.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add cold water to make 1 cup.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in measured liquid. Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Stir in Cool Whip. Refrigerate until Jell-O mounds.
Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Place in 6-cup mold.
Let set.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil
sugar and vinegar for 1 minute.
Pour oil over the vegetables, then pour sugar and vinegar mixture.
Mix well; put in refrigerator overnight.
Keeps a long time.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients together. Fold in the Cool Whip and vanilla.
Pour into crust and chill. Top with serving of Cool Whip and shaved chocolate.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Cook bay leaf, celery and onion until tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Add parsley and bread crumbs.
Mix thoroughly.
To this, add eggs, oysters, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Add milk to oyster liquid to make 1/2 to 2/3 cup of liquid.
Mix all together.
Put in crock-pot and cook for 1 hour on high and 4 hours on low.

title: hot chicken or turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips.
Place in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, salt, water and corn syrup in top of double boiler.

Beat for 1 minute, or until thoroughly blended. Place pan with frosting mixture over boiling water and beat constantly at high speed or with rotary beater for 7 minutes, until frosting stands in stiff peaks.
Stir frosting up from bottom and sides of pan occasionally to be sure it is thoroughly mixed.
Remove from water to a large bowl.
Add vanilla; beat 1 minute more, until thick enough to spread.

title: chili dip(for raw vegetables)
directions: Add chili sauce, lemon juice, ketchup, pepper sauce, salt and pepper to mayonnaise.
Mix well and add sour cream.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: antipasto napoli
directions: Combine tomatoes, mushrooms, sausage, zucchini and artichokes. Add dressing; cover and marinate in refrigerator 2 hours or more. Drain, reserving marinade.
Toss vegetables with greens.
Serve with remaining marinade.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan.

title: spinach and shells
directions: Brown garlic in margarine and remove from heat.
Mix together spinach (cooked and drained well), garlic and Ricotta cheese.
Add to macaroni.
Stir and serve warm.

title: end of garden pickles(sweet)
directions: Place chopped vegetables in a crock. Add the salt.
Let stand overnight at room temperature. Wash in cold water.
Place in pint jars.
Mix vinegar and sugar.
Bring to a boil. Tie the pickling spices up in a thin cloth and put in kettle with the vinegar; cook 1 minute.
Pour over the vegetables, covering the vegetables. Seal.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine the sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt in double boiler.
Add boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Beat egg yolks and gradually pour hot mixture over them while stirring.
Return to double boiler and cook 5 minutes longer.
Just before removing from heat, add lemon juice and rind. Mix well.
Cool and pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Top with a meringue made by beating the 3 egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually add the 6 tablespoons sugar continuing to beat. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil in a large pot, then add vegetables and seasonings; bring to a second boil.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chicken and chips appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, beat together the milk and egg with fork until well mixed.
In a shallow dish, combine the crushed potato chips, onion powder and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces into the egg mixture, then roll them into the potato chip mixture. Arrange coated pieces in a single layer in a baking pan that has been coated with nonstick vegetable spray.
Repeat until all the chicken is coated.
Let sit at room temperature for 15 minutes, then drizzle with melted butter and bake for 10 to 15 minutes, until firm and golden brown.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings (18 to 20 appetizer-sized pieces).

title: m j's killer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (including frosting) with electric mixer. Bake in oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apricot-orange salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add orange juice and mandarin oranges.
Pour into 6 individual molds or 1-quart mold. Chill until set and unmold.

title: sandy's chocolate creme pie
directions: Sift cocoa, flour and sugar together. Beat egg yolks. Add to other mixture with enough milk to wet good. Stir well. Add remaining milk. Stir well. Add vanilla and enough whole milk to fill your pie crust. Cook mixture over low heat, stirring all the time, until it thickens. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: old fashioned chicken dressing
directions: Mix well all ingredients, except Pet milk and milk.
Add Pet milk and some of the chicken broth (save 3 cups chicken broth for Giblet Gravy).
Add sweet milk, enough to make a medium to thin mixture (depending upon how moist a dressing you desire).
Mix well.
Taste to see if you have enough salt and sage.
Remove 2 cups of the mixture, put this to the side for the Giblet Gravy. Pour dressing in a large well-greased roasting pan.
(I use margarine.)
Put a pan of water under your dressing when baking, this will keep from getting too brown on bottom.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together.
One-quarter cup mix can be mixed with 1 cup water.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over butter.
Press down.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, then butterscotch chips. Pour milk evenly over all.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Press lightly. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: rice with shrimp, raisins and walnuts
directions: Cook rice.
Wash the rice once.
Add 4 1/2 cups water, 3 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook on medium to high until water is mostly gone.
Reduce the heat to low and cook for 1/2 hour until done.
Saute the onion in the vegetable oil until golden.
Add shrimp and let cook for a few minutes (shrimp cooks quickly).
Then add walnuts and raisins.
Continue to stir to avoid burning and add salt, pepper and saffron.
Remove from heat. Spread a layer of cooked rice on a large flat dish and top with a layer of the shrimp.
Gently mix.
Continue to layer and mix until everything is on the platter.
Serves 6 to 8 as a main dish.
Best if served fresh.

title: baked scallop casserole
directions: Chop scallops.
Combine wine, salt, onion and scallops in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Drain and reserve 1 cup broth.
Melt butter and blend with flour.
Add reserved broth and cream.
Cook until thick.
Stir in cheese and scallops.
Top with bread crumbs and butter.
Bake in casserole dish for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan and cook onion over moderate heat until soft.
Add broth, salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Add the pumpkin, combine it thoroughly.
Lower the heat and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Add the cream and heat through.
Serve hot!

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add egg and pumpkin.
Blend well. Sift dry ingredients; add to batter, beating well.
Fold in pecans and raisins.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg and milk; coat with crumbs, cheese and basil.
Place in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Microwave on High 18 minutes until tender or bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: busy season casserole
directions: Flour cubed steaks and salt and pepper them before frying. Place in large glass baking dish.
Add a layer of potatoes, onion, salt and pepper (and optional ingredients now if desired).
Mix soups (of your choice) with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over potatoes and onion.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Enjoy!

title: cagerline
directions: Brown the first 4 ingredients together.
Add the tomato sauce and tomato juice.
Bring to boil.
Add most of the noodles; cook 5 minutes.
Add the chopped mushrooms; simmer for 45 minutes without lid.
Stir often.
Add the creamed corn; pour into baking pan. Add cheese on top with ripe olives.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 to 16 large servings.

title: tijuana torte
directions: Brown meat with onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce and water. Place layer of tortillas in casserole (2 or 3) then meat and cheese.
Continue layering, ending with meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: graham cracker square
directions: Put one layer of graham crackers in cookie sheet (10 x 15 1/2 inches).
Put the filling on top of crackers, spreading it evenly on crackers.
Put one more layer of crackers on top of filling.

title: spinach frittata omelet
directions: Saute onion in oil until transparent.
Add spinach; be sure that it's been squeezed dry.
Continue to saute spinach with the onion, stirring constantly to prevent sticking.
Beat eggs thoroughly; add salt, pepper, cheese (Parmesan) and parsley.
Pour over cooked spinach.
Continue to fry eggs and move them around with the spatula to cook inside and top.
When almost set, top with cheese slices.
Cover pan and turn off heat.
Let set for 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: candy bar shakes
directions: Place milk and chopped candy bar in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed for 2 seconds.
Add ice cream.
Cover and blend on low speed about 3 to 5 seconds longer or until smooth.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Melt
chocolate
chips
over double boiler or in microwave. Add butter and pour in milk.
Remove from heat and cool so not to melt marshmallows.

title: kick the can ice cream
directions: You will also need rock salt and both 1 and 3 pound coffee cans.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Prepare 9 x 9-inch dish by greasing with butter.
Boil sugar, salt, milk, vanilla and margarine in heavy pot.
Boil until small bubbles form.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour fudge in pan.
Let set until cool.
Cut into squares.

title: hot chicken salad spread
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Skin and debone chicken.
Grind meat.
Add beaten egg, soda crackers, plenty of broth and enough salt to taste.
Mix real good.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix all 3 ingredients together and pour in a graham cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until firm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the two soups and 1 can chicken broth.
Pour this mixture over chicken, then mix seasoned bread crumbs or stuffing mix with 1 cup chicken broth and melted butter.
Spread on top of soup mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: cactus salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate at least 1 hour. Can be made a day ahead.

title: cheese tarts
directions: You will also need 8 cupcake papers.

title: debbie's candied potatoes
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put into a
10 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and put on top.
Bake 30 minutes with foil on. Bake 10 minutes without the foil.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough and press into the bottom of a baking pan coated with nonstick cooking spray; seal seams and perforations. Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely. In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, Ranch dressing mix and mayonnaise until smooth. Spread over crust. Sprinkle with vegetables and cheese. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving. Cut into squares.

title: barbecue sloppy joes
directions: Fry the hamburger, then mix in the rest of the mixture.
Put into jars; cold pack 1 hour.

title: pretzels
directions: Place pretzels in closed dish.
Pour mixed oil, salad dressing mix and seasoning over pretzels.
Cover.
Let stand 20 minutes. Shake several times to coat evenly.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Fry beef, onion, salt and chili powder together.
Drain. Blend refried beans and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Add to beef.
Then add Pet milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Serve over corn chips.
Then top with chopped lettuce, tomatoes, onions, sour cream and taco sauce.

title: broccoli-tomato salad
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water, just until tender. Drain.
Cool.
Mix cooled broccoli with diced tomato and onion rings.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add mayonnaise and toss until vegetables are coated.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Beat egg yolks; add to cornstarch mixture.
Gradually add boiling water.
Heat to boiling over direct heat, stirring constantly and boil for 4 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add cream of tartar and gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar.
Spread meringue over top of pie carefully, sealing in all the filling by spreading meringue to touch all edges of crust.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 4 to 5 minutes or until browned.
Cool on rack away from draft.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: pheasant pie(favorite recipe of cecil d. andrus, governor of idaho)
directions: Place pheasant in large kettle and cover with water.
Add bay leaf, celery, peppercorns and 1 tablespoon salt.
Bring to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat 2 to 3 hours, or until pheasant is tender.
(Can be done the day before.)
Remove meat from bones; strain broth.
Melt butter in saucepan; add flour and stir until blended.
Gradually add 2 cups of the broth, stirring constantly. Add light cream, pepper and salt.
Cook, stirring until thickened. Arrange pheasant pieces, onions, mushrooms, peas and pimientos in a 2-quart casserole.
Add sauce, leaving at least 1-inch space at top.

title: cherry dumplin' cake(makes 9 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, combine pie filling, condensed milk and almond extract.
In large bowl, cut 1/2 cup oleo into 2 cups biscuit mix until crumbly.
Stir in cherry mixture . Spread in greased 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
In small bowl, combine remaining 1/2 cup biscuit mix and sugar.
Cut in remaining 2 tablespoons oleo until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle evenly over cherry mixture.
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream, if desired.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on box.
Drain tuna.
Stir in tuna and peas.

title: easy chicken and dumplins
directions: Place a whole chicken (minus feathers and other yukky stuff) with a pat of butter on top and 1 cup water in a crock-pot. Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours. Remove chicken from crock-pot and debone. Turn crock-pot to high. Shred or cube chicken.
Depending on how many will be partaking in the meal, place some of the chicken back in the crock-pot.
For a family of 3, I use about 1/3 of the chicken. Add 2 cups water to crock-pot and wait for liquid to boil.
(If in a hurry, transfer to a pot on stove.)

title: meat pie triangle
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Lightly brown meat, breaking up with fork as it cooks.
Transfer meat to bowl with slotted spoon.
Save 2 tablespoons fat to cook onion and garlic until soft.
Add rest of ingredients except egg, cheese, rolls and parsley.
Cook 3 minutes. Stir to blend.
Stir mixture into meat in bowl.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Beat in egg, cheese and parsley.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients, adding just enough boiling water to form a fairly stiff dough.
To fry, heat a little oil in a skillet.
Take a heaping tablespoon of dough and place in skillet. Pat down with back of spoon so it can be turned over and fried on the top side.
If the last few spoons of the cornbread get a little dry, add just a drip or two more water.
Brown on both sides and serve immediately.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.

title: hot ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix oleo, poppy seed, mustard and onion.
Spread on buns.
Add cheese and ham to buns.
Wrap in foil tightly.
Heat and cook 30 minutes at 350°.
Freeze if desired.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Beat all together and freeze.

title: strawberry pretzel
directions: Mix melted margarine with 3 tablespoons sugar and pour over pretzels.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°. Cool 25 to 30 minutes in refrigerator.
Blend 1 cup sugar into cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread on pretzels.
Prepare jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Mix with frozen strawberries. Set in refrigerator until it starts to set.
Pour on top of cream cheese.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut and serve.

title: tiny shrimp triangles
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and gradually blend cream and sherry.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in shrimp, pimiento and salt.
Set aside to cool completely.

title: chocolate chip pound cake(torta di petzo e cioccolata)
directions: From a good friend of my Mom's, Tina.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Mix by hand in a large bowl all the ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured oblong cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until done. When cooled, top with the following icing.

title: sally's nuggets
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, Parmesan cheese, pepper and garlic salt. Dip chicken nuggets in melted butter.
Roll chicken in cracker crumb mixture.
Spray a baking dish with Pam.
Place chicken in dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until chicken is done, but not dry.
Very tasty.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Grease a 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter over low heat; cool.
Cream remaining butter with the cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, creaming until light. Add 1 egg, 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and mix until smooth; set aside.
Beat remaining eggs until fluffy and lemon-colored.
Gradually add remaining sugar, beating until thick.
Fold in remaining flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Then add almond extract, remaining vanilla and the nuts.
Measure 1 cup batter and reserve.
Spread remainder in pan.
Pour cheese mixture over top.
Drop reserved chocolate batter by tablespoons over top.

title: yankee potato salad
directions: Brown bacon lightly.
Add onions; saute slightly.
In another pan, put the warm water, sugar and vinegar.
Heat and make paste out of the flour; add to mixture and stir until thick.
Add bacon and onion; stir well.
Pour over sliced potatoes; refrigerate overnight.
Bake the next day in a 325° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine and cream ingredients together.
Use to line a 9-inch pie pan.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, chicken and dressing mix.
Form into a ball. Roll in pecans.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and wet ingredients separately.
Pour the liquid mixture into the cornmeal mixture.
Stir only enough to combine.
Fill greased baking pan half full.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook chicken bouillon, water, celery, and onion for 20 minutes in large pot with lid on.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Cook another 20 minutes or until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup and cheese cubes.
Heat through until the cheese melts, stirring often.
If too thick, add a little more water.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Soup can be frozen.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Heat 1/4 c. margarine/butter and 1/4 c. shortening in oblong pan, 13 X 9, in 425° oven until melted. Place coated chicken in pan.
Cook uncovered 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; cook uncovered about 30 minutes longer.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix together and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy chicken rice soup
directions: Bring broth to a simmer over low heat.
Add rice and cream. Season with salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cover; cook for 20 minutes, until rice is tender.
Serve hot with parsley sprinkled on top. Serves 4.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Peel and cut apples into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: lemon cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and butter until crumbly. Press into lightly buttered 9 x 13 pan, reserving 1 cup of mix. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool. Beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and
rind until smooth. Spread over cake. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mix. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool. Makes 32 servings.

title: chicken broccoli divan
directions: In shallow casserole, arrange broccoli.
Top with chicken. Combine soup with 1/2 cup of milk and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter with bread crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Cover dish and bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly (an eggbeater works well).
Marinate wings overnight.
If you choose to serve as an entree, you will need approximately 8 chicken wings per person. Heat oven to 400°.
Place wings on broiler pan sprayed with nonstick cooking oil.
Bake for 30 minutes; check often and turn if necessary.

title: champon(japanese noodle soup)
directions: Start water to boil in a large pot.
In wok or iron skillet, pour enough oil to coat. Heat to saute. Add vegetables, individually, except mushrooms. When they begin to wilt, sprinkle with teriyaki sauce. Cover, but stir often.
Add Ramen and flavor packets to boiling water and boil 6 to 8 minutes. When done, turn off and let sit in water.

title: quesadillas
directions: You will need nonstick cooking spray.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Wash and chop broccoli.
Cook about 5 minutes in small amount of water.
If using frozen broccoli, cook according to package directions for 5 minutes; drain.
Combine beaten eggs, soup, cheese, mayonnaise and onions.
Fold into broccoli and pour into greased casserole.
Cover with cracker crumbs and dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fat-free spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix the egg whites, brown sugar, honey and milk.
Blend in the applesauce and vanilla. Add the cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Mix in the flour next, then the oatmeal.
If the batter is runny, add a little more oatmeal.
The batter should be sticky and dense.
Add the raisins. Pour into a nonstick 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown on top.

title: sesame eggplant parmesan(meatless recipe)
directions: Saute eggplant slices in oil over high heat until browned slightly; drain on towels and set aside.
Combine tomatoes, seasonings and grated vegetables in a skillet.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Add Parmesan cheese and sesame seed and blend well.
Place a layer of eggplant in oiled, shallow 2-quart dish.
Cover with 1/2 the tomato sauce, 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes until cheese is melted and begins to brown.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: booky baked crab
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour to make a paste. Remove from heat and stir in milk.
