Cook and stir until very thick and smooth.
Blend a little sauce into egg yolks and return to sauce; mix well.
Mix in salt, pepper, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and crab meat.
Form into 6 patties and place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fried soft crab
directions: Clean soft crabs; paper towel dry.
Dip crabs in white wine. Combine flour, corn meal, salt, pepper and Old Bay.
Coat crabs in flour combination.
Deep fry in Fry Daddy or Grand Pappy.
When crab floats on top, it is done.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, water, salt, ketchup and soy sauce and set aside.
This makes enough sweet and sour sauce for 2 pounds of chicken drummettes.
Roll chicken drummettes in cornstarch.
Brown in Crisco.
Place in baking dish.
Pour mixture over chicken. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 15 minutes.

title: spicy beef and black bean soup
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Add beans, broth, water and salsa.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or longer until beef is tender.
Add peppers, carrots and cook five more minutes.
Garnish with cilantro.

title: peanut candy cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup together and cook to full rolling boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted; then add vanilla and corn flakes and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet and season with salt and pepper.
Place browned chops in casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until chops are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry cheese salad
directions: Cream the cheese, sugar and mayonnaise together and add pineapple, cherries and pecans.
Mix all together thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip and whip in slowly.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: onion beef casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet. Drain off excess grease. Add tomato sauce, flour, onion soup mix and water.
Simmer 5 minutes and add macaroni.
Pour into casserole dish. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat and mix well by stirring.
Serve warm for dipping.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients and set aside.
Mix next seven ingredients (do not sift) and add to first mixture, stirring well. Add water and nuts, mixing well. Bake at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes 3 to 4 loaves, depending on size of pan. Do not fill pans over 2/3 full.

title: the ultimate cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.
When cool, poke cake full of holes.
Drain juice from pineapple and pour over cake.
Mix pineapple, pudding, and Cool Whip together and spread over cake.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Drench in flour.
Brown lightly in skillet with a small amount of oil.
Remove meat.
Add mixture of catsup, bouillon, soy sauce and water to skillet. Simmer 5 minutes.
Return meat to skillet.
Cover and cook over gentle heat until tender (1 1/2 hours).
Add salt and pepper, onion, mushrooms and peppers.
Cover.
Steam until vegetables are just tender.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the chocolate, flour and sugar.
Add milk and mix well. Add eggs.
Next add butter and vanilla.
Beat well after each ingredient.
Cook until thick and pour in pie shell.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add vanilla to butter, then add to egg-sugar mixture.
Add syrup.
Place pecans in crust, then pour syrup mixture over pecans.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: white cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff (set aside).
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix shortening with white sugar and add boiling water.
Alternate this with flour mixture and cold water. Add flavorings.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 (8-inch or two 9-inch) cake layers.

title: d'ascenzo's italian biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add flour in your hands until it becomes a whole piece.
Make a loaf by rolling a piece of the roll (2 or 3).
Take out when brown.
Cut into slices.
Brown once again in the oven on the side.

title: easy popover pancake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat margarine in shallow 1-quart round casserole dish in oven until melted.
Place remaining ingredients in blender in order given.
Cover and blend on high speed 15 seconds.
Scrape sides.
Stir to moisten any remaining flour or beat with hand mixer until smooth.
Pour into casserole dish. Bake until center is puffed and edge is golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with fresh fruit and sweetened whipped cream or yogurt, if desired.

title: baked bananas
directions: Simmer raisins in hot water 10 minutes. Melt butter in pan. Peel and slice bananas lengthwise.
Arrange in single layer in shallow casserole. Cook remainder of ingredients about 10 minutes. Pour over bananas and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Can be sprinkle with coconut.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In large saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in ketchup, vinegar, sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Makes triple recipe.

title: cocktail meat balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine first 9 ingredients and blend well.
Form mixture into small balls, size of walnuts. Arrange balls in baking pan.
In medium saucepan, combine cranberry sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Cook over moderate heat (250°), stirring occasionally until mixture is smooth.
Save less than 1/2 of mixture to dip balls into for serving and pour the rest over meat balls.
Bake 30 minutes. Serve in a chafing dish with toothpicks.
Makes about 60 balls.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine.
Cook to soft ball stage (238°), stirring frequently.
Remove from heat, stir in chocolate pieces.
Add Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: venetian mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms in cool water and remove stems.
Place buttons with centers up on a cookie sheet.
Stuff centers with sausage. Sprinkle on cheese to your preference.
Place in a preheated oven at 250° to 275° and cook until the sausage is done.

title: chocolate-pecan pie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, butter, vanilla and 1 egg in large bowl.
Stir in flour.
Press dough on bottom and 1/2 inch up sides of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over crust.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice in saucepan and cover with water.
Add a dash of salt to rice and let cook until almost dry.
Do not drain.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and set aside.
In saucepan, combine milk, shortening and potatoes.
Cook and stir over low heat until shortening is melted.
Remove from heat and place in large bowl with sugar, salt, 2 cups flour and yeast mixture.
Add eggs and mix well.
Cover loosely and allow to stand for 2 hours (dough will be spongy).
Stir in enough of remaining flour to make soft dough.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Mix in order.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potato wedges
directions: Scrub unpeeled potatoes well.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise, then cut into even wedge.
Boil potato wedges for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain and pat dry.

title: antipasto rice salad
directions: Cool the cooked rice (may be cooked the day before and put in the refrigerator).
Add the Italian dressing, diced ham and turkey, cheese, pepper, onion, black olives and peas.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Add the chopped tomatoes.
Delicious!

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all but the crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 F then top with the crushed potato chips and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: Trim fat from pork.
Cut pork diagonally into 1/4-inch slices. Quickly brown pork slices in hot oil.
Stir constantly. Remove from heat and sprinkle with salt.
Reduce heat. Add asparagus and 1/4 cup water to frying pan and cook, covered, for 5 minutes. Combine soy sauce, garlic, cornstarch, ginger and mace with 1/4 cup water.
Stir into vegetables.
Return pork to pan and cook 3 to 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomatoes and heat through.
Serve with rice.

title: apricot balls
directions: Mix apricots, coconuts and milk.
Shape into 1 inch balls, roll in nuts.
Let stand 2 hours or until firm.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Melt butter; mix all together.
Put 1/2 mixture in bottom of pan.
Add slightly softened ice cream.
Top with remaining mixture.
Freeze.
Serves 24.

title: old-fashioned yeast bread
directions: Mix dry yeast with sugar in warm water and let stand until bubbly.
Scald milk; cool to room temperature, then add salt, vegetable oil and 3 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add yeast mixture and unbleached flour; mix well.
Put dough on lightly floured board and knead until dough is smooth and elastic, at least 10 to 15 minutes.
Put dough into a large greased bowl, turning dough so it is greased on top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (80°) until double in size, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Punch down dough, turn and let rise a second time, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board, divide into 2 sections and let rest for 15 minutes. Make into 2 loaves and put into greased loaf pans and cover.
Let rise again until double and bake in preheated 400° oven for about 50 minutes.
Remove from pans and butter crust for softness.

title: russian salad
directions: In a large stainless cooking pot, combine jello and water. Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and marshmallows.
Put on low heat until blended.
(Use hand mixer to beat while heating.) Take off heat.
Add milk, pineapple and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add lemon juice, bananas and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Chill for several hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: This is a family favorite.
Many variations!

title: mam maw's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix everything except milk and eggs. Mix milk and eggs together. Add to other mixture. Bake in 2 unbaked pie crusts. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: unbaked oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, cocoa, milk and salt and bring to a boil. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal and stir.
Pour into square pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Mix together beef, cottage cheese, eggs, 1/2 cup Parmesan, oregano, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Combine spaghetti sauce, water and parsley.
Spread 1/3 spaghetti sauce in bottom of a 10-inch skillet.
Place 3/4 lasagna noodles over the sauce, breaking to fit flat.
Spread half the filling over the noodles. Sprinkle with half of the remaining Parmesan cheese.
Place half of the Mozzarella over the Parmesan.
Spoon 1/3 of the spaghetti sauce over the cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Cover skillet and cook on low about 45 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: chick 'n pasta soup
directions: Cook chicken, onion and garlic in oil in large saucepan over medium heat, stirring frequently, until chicken loses its pink color and onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except pasta and bring to a boil.
Stir in pasta. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until pasta is tender, about 12 minutes.
Serve with additional Pace picante sauce.
Makes 6 servings, about 8 cups soup.

title: ham and asparagus casserole
directions: Blanch asparagus for 3 minutes in boiling water.
Drain well. Combine asparagus, eggs and ham in 3-quart baking dish. Sprinkle evenly with tapioca. Add cheese, pepper, onion and parsley.
Mix gently. Blend together lemon juice, milk and soup. Add to casserole and mix thoroughly.
Combine bread crumbs and butter. Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: ramen cabbage salad
directions: *Brown lightly in oven.

title: coconut pie
directions: Pour the milk over coconut and let set awhile.
Beat butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk, coconut and flavoring.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pop the popcorn.
Place in a large buttered pan.
Melt marshmallows and oleo.
Add vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and mix thoroughly.
Press in Bundt cake pan.
Turn out on plate. Enjoy!

title: smores
directions: Melt to boil, corn syrup, margarine and chocolate chips.
Add Vanilla.
Pour over cereal.
Stir in marshmallows.

title: nutritious cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/4 cups flour and the next 6 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed until blended, then by hand, stir in 1 cup flour, oatmeal, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon, 2 inches apart, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: tess' bean pot
directions: Drain all but baked beans.
Brown onions and bacon.
Add brown sugar, catsup, garlic powder, prepared mustard, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine all and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans to cover ball.
Great for parties!

title: apple and black walnut cream
directions: Combine the yogurt, lemon juice and honey; mixing well to blend.
Shred apples into yogurt mixture, stirring after each addition to prevent discoloration.
Stir in nuts and serve immediately.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar in a small bowl.
Cover and let stand at room temperature.
Mix sugar and egg yolk in a small saucepan.
Add mustard and vinegar.
Mix and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Cover and chill. Serve at room temperature.

title: coffee jello dessert
directions: In medium size bowl, soak gelatin in 1/4 cup cold coffee.
Heat remaining to just boiling.
Dissolve sugar in hot coffee.
Stir well.
Add to gelatin and stir again.
Refrigerate until set. Serve topped with plain or chocolate Cool Whip.

title: green chili cheese rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed; mix sour cream, chiles and rice and seasonings together in bowl.
Mix it well.

title: melting moments cookies(this recipe is 51 years old)
directions: Cream 1 cup butter and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Add cornstarch and flour.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Do not brown.
Combine rest of ingredients and frost when cool.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in flour, salt and soda.
Stir in chips. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: christmas crisp balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and chopped dates.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts, coconut, and Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Yield: 60 balls.

title: quail in a bag
directions: Place flour in 10 x 16-inch roasting bag; place bag in 2-inch deep roasting pan.
Combine wine and bouquet sauce.
Pour into bag and mix well with flour.
Add celery and mushrooms with liquid to bag.
Brush quail halves with butter and season with salt.
Place quail on vegetables in bag.
Close with twist tie and cut 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top of bag.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Serve bag gravy over quail.
Serves 4.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Saute meat and unions until meat is no longer red.
Add cabbage and 1/2 of soy sauce and about 1/2 cup of water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add sprouts, remainder of sauce and water, if needed. Simmer until meat and vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place spareribs, meat side up in a 9x13-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Top with lemon slices and chopped onion.

title: sausage cornbread dressing
directions: Brown sausage and add butter, eggs and bread crumbs. Add all other ingredients. Add broth until moist. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: baked fish
directions: Place fish in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brush with a little oil.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Add mushrooms and artichokes; spoon Eggplant-Tomato Sauce over all.
Cover; return to oven and bake 20 minutes.
Uncover, bake 5 minutes more.
Serve with hot cooked rice, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients (with exception of sugar).
Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat after each addition.
Add dry ingredients to this mixture.
Mix well.
Add carrots, nuts and pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: lemon squares
directions: Bake 20 minutes at 350°. If using Pyrex, 325°. When baked, sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Loosen from sides of pan with sharp knife. Cool 20 minutes. Then cut into squares. Freezes well. Can be served from freezer.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters and roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture (1/2 cup sugar).
Pile in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Melt margarine; add sugar and cinnamon (3/4 cup sugar).
Heat until sugar melts and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: cheese and onion potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt Parkay over medium heat.
Add potatoes, onions and pepper; toss to coat.
Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 10 minutes.
Uncover; cook until potatoes are browned, about 2 to 5 minutes.
Top with cheese. Cover and remove from heat; let stand for few minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Yields 4 servings (good with steak).

title: whipped cream pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo.
Using an electric mixer, add one egg at a time; add flour and whipping cream alternately while mixing and add flavorings.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf, Bundt, tube or 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack.

title: chocolate bit bar
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs together.
Add and stir in flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in chocolate bits and walnuts.
Spread in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. When cooled, cut in slices.
Baked product will sink in the middle.

title: texas corn
directions: Heat corn to boiling, stir in cream cheese, heated corn will melt cream cheese.
Add chopped green chilies.
May double or triple.
Excellent with turkey, great to take for potluck dinners.

title: shake-a-sack snack
directions: In a medium paper sack or a large plastic bag, combine the cheese crackers, oyster crackers, the dry buttermilk salad dressing mix and the oregano.
Close back and shake well, then pour the oil in the mixture and shake well again.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar. Add eggs one at a time. Sift dry ingredients, including cocoa. Add alternately with milk. Add vanilla. Bake in greased Bundt pan (or undivided tube pan) at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Do not open oven door until time is up!!!!! Cool in pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion in margarine.
Add catsup, chili powder and brown sugar.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour over cooked meat.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Layer cabbage and onions in very large bowl.
Put vinegar, sugar and spices in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Mix in salad oil and pour over contents of bowl.
Stir occasionally for several hours.
Best if made 1 to 2 days in advance.
Does not require refrigeration.

title: ohio buckeyes
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
In a large casserole dish, mix beef mixture with soups, beans, mushrooms and spices. Spread evenly in dish.
Top with layer of Tater Tots.
Top Tater Tots evenly with shredded cheese.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake another 15 minutes or until browned.

title: lemony glazed vegetables
directions: In a pan on top of stove, saute broccoli in oil until tender-crisp.
Remove from pan.
Stir in carrots; saute until tender-crisp.
Stir in mushrooms; saute lightly.
Return broccoli to skillet.
Stir in lemon.
Combine butter and sugar; add to vegetables.
Stir until vegetables are well glazed.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer.
Add eggs until blended.

title: heavenly hot cakes
directions: Measure into bowl 2/3 cup warm water and sprinkle in 2 packages yeast, stirring until dissolved.
Add biscuit mix, milk and egg.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Bake pancakes on hot griddle, lightly greased.
Turn only once when bubbles appear and edges become dry.
Serve with butter and syrup.
Makes about 12 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Add soup, milk, 1/2 of the butter and onions.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 of onions and butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sauerbraten with dumplings
directions: Place meat in a dish.
Mix onions, bay leaves, peppercorns, cloves, juniper berries, salt, vinegar and water; pour over meat. Cover tightly and refrigerate 3 days, turning several times. Remove meat and brown.
Save the marinade.
Add marinade to meat in skillet, cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Remove meat; remove onions.
Strain liquid and drippings in skillet.
Measure and add water to measure 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Add cabbage, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in gingersnaps and sugar; simmer 3 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add rice, seasoning packet, onion soup and water.
Simmer 1 minute; add chestnuts and mushrooms.
Pour into slightly greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Last 15 minutes, sprinkle chopped pecans over top of casserole.

title: lemon-roasted duck
directions: Wash the ducks inside and out and dry completely.
Salt and pepper.
Melt butter in roasting pan; brown ducks on all sides on top of stove.
Pour lemon juice in cavities of ducks and put rinds around sides.
Cook, covered, in 300° oven until tender.
Remove meat from bones and pour gravy in pan over meat.
Serves 6.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Beat eggs in a small mixer bowl.
Blend in sugar and melted butter or margarine.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until almost set (pie will not test done).

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 inch pan. Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients in order listed.
Press firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Chill thoroughly if desired.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: tortellini minestrone
directions: This soup thickens as it stands; add a bit more broth if thinner soup is desired.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir together evaporated milk, corn syrup, chocolate and butter or margarine.
Stirring constantly, cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until chocolate is completely melted and mixture is well blended and slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool to room temperature.
Serve over ice cream or cake.
Store in a tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Before serving, reheat in small saucepan, stirring constantly.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: spiced chicken
directions: Combine orange juice and peaches with next 5 ingredients in saucepan and cook slowly for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, dredge chicken in seasoned flour and brown in hot oil in large pan. Remove chicken, just to pour off oil, retaining flavory bits in skillet.
Replace chicken and pour fruit sauce over top.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Put in a casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan toffee
directions: Line 15 x 10-inch pan with heavy foil. Lightly grease foil. Sprinkle 1 cup pecans to within 1-inch of edges.

title: baked beans
directions: Take 1 medium can of baked beans.
Add some brown sugar, some ketchup and chopped onion.
Lay bacon strips on top of beans and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Peel onions and cucumbers and slice in medium size bowl. Cover with cold water and add 1/4 cup table salt.
Soak approximately 2 hours.
Drain well.
Add Miracle Whip and vinegar to taste.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water, molasses and salt until sugar melts. Add the butter and cook until spins a thread.
Pour over the popcorn and make into balls.

title: cherry torte
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla and continue beating.
Fold in broken saltines and chopped nuts.
Spread in a greased 11 x 15-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 325°.
When cooled, spread on the Dream Whip, prepared according to directions.
Top with cherry pie filling and chill at least 2 hours before serving.
This will keep 5 days in refrigerator and still be firm.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop peppers, onions, tomatoes and cabbage as fine as you like it.
Mix in salt and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Mix vinegar, spices (tie pickling spice in cloth), and sugar and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add the chopped mixture and continue to simmer for another 25 minutes.
Place mixture in hot jars and seal.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Spray mini muffin tin with nonstick spray.
Spoon cookie dough in each section, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Dough will rise up like muffins.
Remove from oven and immediately push 1 Reese's cup into each cookie.
Return to oven for 2 minutes.
Cool in pan 3 to 5 minutes before moving to wire rack.

title: easy little cheesecakes
directions: Line 12 muffin tins with foil liners.
Place 1 wafer in each cup.
Mix cheese, vanilla and sugar at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Top with fruit, melted chocolate, etc.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Place in 1 1/2-quart Pyrex dish. Bring broth and cream of celery soup to a boil.
Mix thoroughly. Combine flour, melted butter and buttermilk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
(This makes the crust.)
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: sweet and sour vegetables
directions: Cook sugar, vinegar, flour and mustard until thick.
Cool. Drain vegetables and beans.
Add the chopped vegetables.
Pour the cooked dressing over all and mix.
Store in the refrigerator overnight.
Will keep for 1 week when refrigerated.

title: golden mushroom chicken
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over chicken in casserole.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve with buttered noodles.

title: taco soup
directions: In a dutch oven or large sauce pan cook beef and chopped onions until the beef is no longer pink. Drain then stir in taco seasoning, corn, beans and tomatoes. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until heated thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Place tortilla chips in soup bowls, ladle soup over chips and sprinkle with cheese. Serve with warm tortillas.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
In dripper pan roll hamburger in shells.
Pour cream of chicken soup, diluted with water, over shells.
Pour tomato soup, undiluted, combined with enchilada sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until boiling around edges.
Serve with chopped lettuce on top.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: white beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in at least double amount of water.
Next day, bring to a boil, drop in bouillon cubes and onion (if desired).
Cook until tender.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix and serve in a hollowed-out pumpernickel round loaf.
Use hollowed out bread in bite size pieces to dip.
Will make 2 to 3 cups.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs in serving size pieces; brown in frying pan, then wrap in paper toweling to remove excess grease.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, Durkee sauce and a little brown sugar.
Slice onions over ribs; gradually add spaghetti sauce. Cover and bake at 325° to 350° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: russian tea
directions: Simmer 1 hour.
If need of storing in refrigerator, strain out spices.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: turkey burgers parmigiana
directions: Combine chicken broth, tomato sauce and dried whole oregano in a small bowl.
Stir well and set aside.
Combine turkey, parsley, poultry seasoning, pepper and garlic in a medium bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Divide mixture into 4 equal portions shaping each into a 1/2 inch thick oval patty.
Sprinkle breadcrumbs on a sheet of wax paper.
Press patties in breadcrumbs, lightly coating each side.
Place patties in a shallow baking dish coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes; drain.
Turn patties over and spoon tomato mixture evenly over patties.
Bake an additional 8 minutes or until sauce is bubbly.
Sprinkle patties with cheese and bake 1 additional minute or until cheese is melted. Garnish with parsley.

title: coffee punch
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Stir milk and ice cream into the first mixture. Serve.

title: cornbread extravaganza
directions: Make cornbread a day ahead; let cool thoroughly.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and dry dressing mix; set aside.
Combine tomatoes, onions and peppers; set aside.
Place 1/2 crumbled cornbread in bottom of 4-quart serving dish.
Top with 1/2 of beans and 1/2 of the combined tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Add 1/2 of the cheese, 1/2 the bacon and 1/2 of the corn.
Spread 1/2 of the dressing mixture over top.
Repeat the layers, leaving enough cornbread for a light covering over the mixture.
Garnish with green pepper rings and sliced tomatoes.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Beat when chilled overnight.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes, then add Jell-O and a few drops of red food coloring. Cool.
Add strawberries and pour into cooked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip. For 2 pies, buy 3 pints of berries.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat 1/3 cup sugar into egg yolks.
Add salt; stir in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats spoon.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 3 tablespoons sugar, beating to soft peaks.
Add to custard and mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.
Pour into punch bowl or cups.
Serve with whipped cream and nutmeg.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chex party mix
directions: Melt oleo in a large roasting pan.
Stir in salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add cereal and nuts.
Mix until all pieces are coated.
Heat in 250° oven for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes. Spread on paper towels to cool.
Makes about 9 cups.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Add well beaten eggs last.
Dough will be stiff.
Mix flour in with hands.
Pat down on cookie sheet with a fork.
Bake slowly, as they burn easily, at 300°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown and thick.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour, cream of tarter, baking soda and salt together.
Mix all ingredients, mixing well.
Form into 1-inch balls and coat with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8-9 min.
Cookies will be a light brown when done.

title: game sandwich
directions: Mix in cereal bowl.
Spread mixture on bun tops.
Layer baked ham or chipped, chopped ham.
Fold Swiss cheese over meat. Wrap in foil and heat in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Set aside and let steep.
Strain out cranberries.
To what's left, add juices of oranges and lemons.
Add sugar.
Serve warm with 1 stick cinnamon in cup.

title: vivien's lime jello-vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients. When thickened, fold in whipped canned milk; chill.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and press in pan sprayed with Pam. Bake for 1 hour in slow oven at 300°.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and salt.
Mix together vinegar, egg and water.
Add flour; mix until easy to work with.
Add more flour if necessary.
Chill at least 1 hour before using.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix eggs until foamy. Slowly add sugar and beat until thick. Add cool whip, vanilla, salt and eagle brand milk.

title: roasted trout in bacon
directions: Combine all ingredients except fish and bacon; mix well. Brush mixture inside and out of fish.
Place fish in a buttered baking dish.
Score skin with sharp knife in 2 or 3 places.
Wrap with bacon strips.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Baste with pan juices often.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar together until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour, a little at a time, with milk and sour cream.
Fold in on lowest cycle on mixer.
Add vanilla; pour in a well greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° about 2 hours.

title: homemade bread
directions: Stir ingredients together in order given, pouring liquids into flour.
Add a little warm water if necessary.

title: asparagus stir-fry tomato
directions: Stir water into cornstarch.
Stir in soy sauce and salt.
Set aside.
Snap off and discard woody bases from asparagus.
Bias slice asparagus clockwise into 1 1/2-inch lengths.
(If asparagus is not young and tender, precook 4 to 5 minutes.)

title: my favorite shake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until all ice is crushed and malted is thick.

title: chili con carne
directions: Saute onions in oil until tender.
Add ground beef and brown. Add seasonings, tomatoes and kidney beans.
Stir.
Add beer and stir.
Simmer slowly, covered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until thick.
Remove lid and simmer, uncovered, if necessary.
Serve with rice, grated cheese and sour cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together to make sauce.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer broccoli, grated cheese, sauce and onions (turkey, chicken, ham, etc., if desired; if meat is used, use only one package of broccoli).
Cover with stuffing mix, make another layer putting remainder of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix above vegetables together.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole for 20 minutes at 350°.
During last 10 minutes, sprinkle shredded cheese on top.

title: dutch chocolate cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, sift together sugar and flour. Combine margarine, shortening, cocoa and water in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture and mix well. Cool a little and add buttermilk, soda, vanilla, eggs and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Make small balls and roll in sifted powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook!

title: poor man cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water 10 to 15 minutes.
Add Crisco.
Mix together other ingredients.
Stir in raisins, water and Crisco mixture.
Spread on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook sauce until well blended (about 10 minutes).
Garlic and onion juice may be added.
(I usually put in my sauce.)

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Put shredded cabbage in bowl.
You may add grated carrots, bell pepper, cheese and a little onion if desired.
Mix salad dressing, vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed in a cup and beat it up with spoon and then pour over cabbage and toss.
Sometime, if you want to, you can toss just before putting it on the table for the meal.

title: layered ground beef casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, layer half the onion, celery and green pepper; season with salt and pepper.
Top with beef; season 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Pour on tomato sauce.
Top with remaining onion, celery and green pepper; season with salt and pepper.
Arrange potatoes over top; spread with soup.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until potatoes are tender and top is slightly browned.
Do not stir.
Makes 6 servings.
Can be made a day ahead and reheated.
Freezes well. Thaw, then cover and reheat in 350° oven.

title: coconut cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix and bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Leave cake in pan and punch holes in top.
Spread Eagle Brand milk over top of cake; let cool.
Spread cream of coconut over cake.
Now spread Cool Whip.
Last spread coconut over Cool Whip. Cover tightly and refrigerate for 2 or 3 days before serving.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Mix flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Mix sour cream and jam together. Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Put in 5 small greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Can be frosted with a thin white icing drizzled over top.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing(for green salads)
directions: Whip in blender the oil, vinegar and sugar.
Add celery salt and catsup.
Use over green salad.
Refrigerate.
Shake before use. (It can separate.)

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Bruise the spices and tea in a muslin bag.
Boil with vinegar and sugar for 5 minutes.
Pour over the rind and let it stand 24 hours.
Remove the liquid and after heating it, pour over the rind again and let stand for another 24 hours, after which, boil all together for a short time.

title: caramel apple bread pudding
directions: Melt caramels with water in saucepan over low heat.
Stir occasionally until sauce is smooth.
Place bread cubes in greased 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with apple slices.
Combine eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla, salt and cinnamon; pour over apples. Cover with caramel sauce.
Set dish in large pan on oven rack; pour in boiling water to 1/2-inch depth.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and outside edge comes out clean.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle orange Jell-O over cottage cheese and mix.
Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix with cottage cheese and dry Jell-O. Fold in Cool Whip and set in refrigerator about 1 hour before serving.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and blend all ingredients together and pour in baking dish.

title: monster cookies
directions: In a large bowl cream eggs, butter and sugar together. Add peanut butter, vanilla, karo syrup and baking soda. Mix well. Add remaining ingredients, use a rounded tablespoon of dough per cookie. Bake at 350 degrees for 16 minutes. Leave in pan approx. 2 minutes after taking off of pan. Makes about 4 dozen. If you want a thicker cookie refrigerate dough overnight.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in greased baking dish.
Bake in 275° oven for 3 hours.
During the first hour, stir frequently.
During last half hour add 1/2 cup raisins.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Cream shortening in mixing bowl.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Add milk and food coloring.

title: lemon sunshine cake
directions: Beat together first 6 ingredients until very thick.
Stir in flour.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until foamy. Slowly add 1 cup of sugar; beat until stiff glossy peaks form. Gradually beat yolk mixture into egg whites.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Invert cake to cool.
Cut cooled cake into 3 layers.
Dust top with confectioners sugar.

title: cabbage hot dish
directions: Place shredded cabbage in greased baking dish.
Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Stir in uncooked rice.
Place meat and rice mixture on cabbage, then cover with tomato soup and 1 can of water.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Serves 6.
Serve with salad and hot rolls.
Dish is low in calories, yet filling.

title: frosted pecans
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat water and egg white until frothy.
Mix pecans in.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and salt. Add to pecan mixture, mixing well.
Spray baking sheet with Pam. Spread pecans on baking sheet; bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
(I like these for Christmas gifts, just put in glass jar and add a ribbon.)

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil; simmer for 5 minutes. Add margarine.
Mix the cornstarch with a little cold water until dissolved and add this to mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie crust; top with crust.
Bake at 350° until top crust browns.

title: dad's hot mull cider
directions: Heat first two ingredients in carafe.
Add brandy to taste.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: Mix together the margarine, flour and pecans.
Pat in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: noodles
directions: Beat until frothy.
Gradually add flour until you have a soft but not sticky dough.
The last bit of flour you add, I usually knead with my hands.
Roll out into a circle; let dry 2 to 3 hours. Cut into strips, then slice as thin as you want.
Add to boiling broth.
Cook until done.

title: banana bread muffins
directions: Mash bananas.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt and sugar. Beat eggs and pour in with oil and nuts.
Pour in muffin tin of loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 14 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly around the edges.
Yields 6 servings.

title: rainbow gelatin(10 layer)
directions: Dissolve 1 package gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Pour 2/3 cup gelatin into mold or 8 x 8-inch pan; refrigerate and let set. Add 2 tablespoons sour cream to remaining 1/3 cup hot dissolved gelatin and beat.
Pour and spread over first layer.
Repeat procedure with 4 other packages.
It will take about 1 hour for the first layer to set, but after that layers set fast.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown chopped meat and chopped onion and add salt and pepper as you desire.
Meanwhile, cut tops off peppers and clean.
Cut out middle stem from top.
Boil the bagged rice.
Drain chopped meat from grease and add rice; mix.
Spoon into the peppers.
Put in pot.
Add stewed tomatoes around peppers.
Put tops of peppers on each pepper and put a tomato on each.
Add 1/2 cup of water to pot and let simmer until they feel soft.
Serve.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Mix together the cottage cheese and jello.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Let stand overnight.

title: dianna's potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients.
add chips and nuts last.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: ripe tomato ketchup
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together. Cook down low and seal in hot jars. This is the ketchup we eat with dried beans.

title: whole wheat rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar and shortening. Add cold water and beaten eggs. When cool, add yeast, salt and flour (small amount at a time), stirring well. Let rise 3 hours. Make into rolls (let rise 2 more hours) or store in refrigerator until ready to use. You can make all rolls out at once and freeze. They freeze well. DO NOT CROWD TOO CLOSE IN PAN WHEN BAKING. Bake at 400° until brown and done.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in salty water until slightly soft.
Rinse in ice water.
Arrange layers of carrots, green pepper and onion in bowl or container with lid.
Combine all ingredients (remaining) in a saucepan and bring to boil, stirring until thoroughly blended. Pour over carrot mixture and refrigerate until flavor is absorbed, 24 hours.
Will keep 2 weeks if kept cold.

title: kissy cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Mix. Drop by spoon on a cookie sheet. Press on a Kiss and mold dough around.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 60 to 90 cookies.

title: spaghetti red
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Place all ingredients in a large kettle; cook over medium heat until spaghetti is tender.
Add water if necessary.
This recipe gets better the more its cooked.

title: biscuit tortoni(dessert)
directions: Whip cream and sugar until stiff.
In separate bowl, dissolve coffee in rum.
Gently fold into whipped cream mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into cream mixture.
Spoon into fluted cupcake holder until filled (or use parfait glasses).
Sprinkle top with nuts and place a cherry on top.
Cover with Saran Wrap and then foil and place in freezer until frozen.
(May be kept up to 4 weeks in freezer.)
Remove from freezer just before serving.
Can also be made in cake pan with ladyfingers all around outside.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix everything except buttermilk and flour, then add buttermilk.
Mix it and then add flour.
Add ginger to taste. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: chops and rice
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and water.
Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until chops are tender.
Place rice in center of platter and arrange chops around rice.
Pour tomatoes over chops and rice.

title: stir and drop cookies
directions: Beat eggs until well blended.
Stir in oil, vanilla and lemon juice.
Blend in sugar and beat until mixture thickens.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Dough will be soft.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets 1 inch apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: whiskey or bourbon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into small balls.
If balls then to crumble, add a few
extra
drops
of
bourbon
to
the mixture. Roll each in
powdered
sugar
and
store in airtight container for about a week
to
ripen.
Makes
4 dozen 1/2-inch balls with approximately 60 calories per serving.

title: sunday roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast lightly. Place in large baking dish. Add potato wedges and carrots, placing on each side. Sprinkle soup mix over roast, potatoes and carrots. Cover with foil. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Turn oven to 250° when you leave for Sunday School. Roast will be ready when you return. Remove roast, carrots and potatoes. Add 2 tablespoons flour to 6 ounces of water; stir until mixed well. Pour into drippings. Makes very good gravy.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: Marinate 2 pounds boiled shrimp or vegetables and serve over a nest of lettuce.

title: monkey bread(best when eaten warm.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix white sugar and cinnamon. Cut biscuits into 1/4. Roll 1/4 into balls. Put balls in mix sugar and cinnamon. Make sure balls are covered with mixture. Put in greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle light brown sugar over mix. Pour stick of melted margarine over mix. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes. When done, turn upside down on plate.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: In a

large pan, saute the onion, bell pepper and sausage until tender. Drain. Add cabbage, Ro-Tel tomatoes and tomato sauce. Crumble bacon over all. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover and cook over medium heat until cabbage is tender, about 45 minutes.

title: herbed shrimp dip
directions: In bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese with sour cream until very smooth. Stir in scallion, parsley, tarragon, zest, garlic powder, salt, pepper and Tabasco until combined. Stir in shrimp. Chill at least 1 hour. With serrated knife, horizontally cut off top 1/3 from top of bread. With small knife, cut around inside edge of bread. Pull out bread in large pieces, leaving 1/2-inch thick shell. Cut bread top and pieces into 1-inch cubes. Just before serving, place loaf on serving platter. Fill with dip. Serve with bread cubes and vegetables. Makes 24 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together in large baking dish.
Cover with stuffing and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°
or until bubblicious.

title: dandelion root coffee
directions: Place roots on cookie sheet in single layer.
Dry at 225° for 4 to 5 hours until roots are brittle and brown inside.
Grind in coffee grinder and brew as coffee, using 1/4 less dandelion coffee as you would brew regular coffee.

title: spicy christmas pickles
directions: Drain juice from pickles and discard. Slice pickles into spears and put in jar. Add hot sauce, garlic and 1/3 of sugar. Screw on lid tightly. Gently mix pickles with sugar and spices by tipping jar back and forth. Leave on counter at room temperature for 1 week. As sugar dissolves, add more sugar until all sugar is used. Mix pickles daily. Pickles will be dark green when all sugar is absorbed.

title: sweet zucchini red pickle
directions: Add lime and 8 1/2 quarts water to zucchini.
Let stand 24 hours.
Pour
off water.
Rinse, then soak 3 more hours in plain water (not community water).
Rinse very well and drain. Mix
1 cup vinegar, alum and food coloring in large pan.
Then add zucchini
and enough plain water (not community water) to cover. Simmer
for
hours.
Meanwhile
mix
and bring to a boil, cinnamon,
2 cups vinegar, 3 cups plain water, red hots and
9 cups
sugar.
Drain
first
mixture
off and pour this second one over
zucchini.
Everyday
for
days, drain and bring liquid to a
boil,
then
pour back over zucchini.
The second day add 1 more
cup
vinegar
and 2 more cups sugar to liquid.
The third day bring liquid to boil and heat zucchini. Pack zucchini into jars and pour boiling liquid over zucchini. Then seal.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring to boil.
Boil hard 3 minutes and add dash of salt and teaspoon vanilla.
Drop by Tbsp on waxed paper.

title: elephant ears
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Flatten out with hand to the size of a pancake and fry in deep fat until golden brown. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar or powdered sugar.

title: fattigmann
directions: Beat egg and egg yolk slightly; add sugar and water and beat. Add cardamom to 1/2 cup flour; add this mixture to the beaten eggs. Continue adding flour until the dough handles easily without sticking.
Roll small portion of dough very thin.
Cut into diamonds and fry in deep fat.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar as soon as you remove them from the fat.

title: yummy vegetable casserole
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Mix all ingredients together, except butter and crackers.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Melt butter.
Mix with cracker crumbs.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° until top is brown and bubbly.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lotsa pepper relish(makes 6 one-cup jars)
directions: Stem and halve peppers; discard seeds.
(It's best to wear plastic gloves when handling hot peppers.)
Finely chop peppers and measure 4 cups mixed peppers into a 6 or 8-quart saucepan.
Stir in vinegar.
Measure sugar into a separate bowl and set aside.
Stir pectin into peppers, then add margarine.
Bring mixture to full, rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Quickly stir in sugar.
Return to full boil and boil exactly 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Skim off any foam with a metal spoon.
Quickly ladle mixture into hot clean jars, filling to within 1/8-inch of top.
Wipe jar rims and threads.
Cover with 2 piece lid.
Screw on bands until tight.
Invert jar 5 minutes, then turn upright.
Cool 1 to 1 1/2 hours, then shake jars gently to distribute peppers evenly.
Check seals after jars cool.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine
egg,
bread	crumbs, onion, 1 can tomato sauce, oregano, salt and pepper.
Mix well and
add meat.
Mix well and shape into a flat rectangle about 10
to
12 inches
on	waxed paper.
Sprinkle shredded cheese evenly
over the meat.
Roll like a jelly roll.	Press ends to seal.
Place
on rack in a shallow baking dish.
Bake 1 hour. Drain
off excess fat.
Pour on remaining can of tomato sauce. Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: chicken-pineapple-walnut stir fry
directions: Drain pineapple saving syrup. Pour hot water over walnuts let stand 2 minutes and drain. Heat 2 tablespoons oil in wok or skillet. Stir fry walnuts until brown, remove and drain. Add oil if needed, stir fry chicken, onions, garlic, ginger until chicken turns white. Add broccoli and cook until tender but crisp. Return chicken, nuts and pineapple with syrup from pineapple, soy sauce and corn starch. Cook until thicken. Serve with rice or plain. 4 to 6 servings.

title: tuna cutlets
directions: Melt Crisco.
Add flour and milk; cook until thick.
Put tuna in bowl and add rest of ingredients.
Mix well; form into cutlets. Dip into 1 slightly beaten egg and cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Fry in hot fat.

title: shrimp joe
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In saucepan, mix all ingredients except shrimp.
Heat until butter melts.
Heat in oven until shrimp turns pink, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Prepare rice according to package directions using bouillon cubes, soy sauce and white pepper.
Parboil pea pods.
Toss pods with rice.
Serve shrimp over rice.

title: mom's shipwreck stew
directions: Brown hamburger with sauteed onions.
Then layer ingredients. Cook 1 1/2 hours on top of stove on medium to low heat.

title: sweet potato daisy biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine baking mix and orange peel; cut in cream cheese until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add sweet potatoes and milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough out onto surface dusted with baking mix.
Shape into ball; knead 4 to 5 times.
Roll dough 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with cutters dipped in baking mix.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.

With sharp knife dipped in baking mix, cut six 1/2 inch lashes around edge of each biscuit to form petals. Using thumb, make indentation in center of each biscuit and fill with about 1/4 teaspoon of marmalade.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli puffs
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; drain well and set aside. In medium bowl, beat egg yolks; add flour and mix well.
Stir in mayo, butter, salt, pepper, nutmeg and cheese.
Stir in broccoli; mix gently.
Beat egg whites to stiff peaks and stir in gently the broccoli mixture.
Put in 9-inch square baking pan that is well-greased.
Bake in 350° oven (preheated) for 30 minutes.

title: chicken kieve
directions: Mix egg, cheese and onion.
Dip breasts in egg mixture, then flour.
Fry in 1/4 cup margarine for 3 to 4 minutes each side. Cook 1 1/2 cups cooked rice.
Place chicken over rice and cover with chicken soup (gravy).

title: 2 x 4
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a pot. Before serving, melt Velveeta into mixture.

title: arkansas cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and mix.
Add buttermilk and stir.
Add flour, soda and cinnamon. Add diced apples.
When mixed, spread mixture into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool and frost.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter and 4 squares chocolate.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Blend in 2 cups sugar, 4 eggs, one at a time. Beat 1 minute.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts; put in all dry ingredients.
Mix well; chill at least 15 minutes.
Shape in little balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 300° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Place broccoli flowerets in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add water to cover.
Boil gently for 7 minutes.
Drain.
Place flowerets and chicken cubes in a 13 1/2 x 9-inch baking pan, evenly distributing both.
Sprinkle cheese over them.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature. Mix all ingredients except walnuts together and roll into ball. Chill. Roll in walnuts.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Put in a mixing bowl and blend the ingredients until light and fluffy.
Pour mixture in a casserole dish and add topping.

title: marinated chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle meat tenderizer on meat.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Place roast in Ziploc bag.
Pour mixture in; let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Cook over medium heat on grill until done.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, eggnog, oleo, rum extract and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. Stir until moist. Pour in greased or sprayed loaf pan. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. Cool 10 minutes in pan before cooling on rack.

title: quick chili
directions: Bring mixed ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour. Do not stir.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: To the cream cheese add margarine, vanilla and confectioners sugar, beating well after each ingredient is added.
After frosting the cake, garnish with nuts.

title: fruit salad lush
directions: Fold the Dream Whip with fruit.
Serve as a salad or dessert. Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Slice sausage into bite size pieces.
Combine mustard and jelly into a pan; heat until both are dissolved, making a sweet and sour sauce.
Pour over sausages; heat until sausages are warm.
Serve with toothpicks as an appetizer or with rice as a main course.

title: beef stroganoff(serves 4)
directions: Dip meat in flour.
In heavy skillet, brown meat in hot fat. Add onion, garlic and mushrooms (include liquid).
Combine all other ingredients except sour cream and pour over meat mixture. Cover and simmer for about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Add a little water if too much liquid evaporates.
Stir in sour cream. Heat but do not boil.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chiffon salad
directions: Mix jello with drained pineapple; stir thoroughly.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Stir well.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Slice meat diagonally into thin strips.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and ginger; stir into soy sauce.
Pour mixture over meat. Stir; marinate for several hours or overnight.
Cut peppers into wedges.
Quickly brown meat in hot oil, about half at a time; remove from pan and keep warm.
Lower heat; add peppers, garlic and water.
cook until peppers are tender crisp (5 minutes).
Stir meat back back into pan; add tomatoes.
Heat and serve.
Good served over rice.
Can be made in crock-pot.
Also stew beef can be used instead of steak.

title: kifles
directions: Combine sour cream and boiling water; mix well.
Stir in yeast. Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir until yeast is completely dissolved; set aside.
Place butter and 1/2 cup flour in small bowl.
Add sour cream mixture and beat 1 minute at low speed.
Add egg yolks and 1/4 cup of flour; beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Stir in the remaining flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured surface; knead for 8 to 10 minutes.
Divide into 3 balls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill for 2 hours or up to 5 days.
When ready to shape, combine nuts, sugar and vanilla.
Fold in the whipped egg whites. On a dusted surface with confectioners sugar, roll each ball of dough into a 10-inch circle; cut each into 12 wedges.
Top wide edges with 1 teaspoon of filling.
Roll from wide edge.
Place on greased baking sheets, with points underneath.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: mother's prince cake
directions: Cream together the butter with the sugar. Add egg and molasses with soda. Stir in the buttermilk. Sift together the flour, allspice, baking powder and cinnamon. Stir into the mixture and beat well. Add the raisins and nuts. Bake in 3 layers. Allow layers to be thoroughly cold before icing.

title: bulk biscuit mix
directions: For biscuit mix:
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a lrg. bowl and mix well.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until particles are fine.
Store at room temperature in an airtight container.
For 12 biscuits, preheat oven to 450°.
Place 2-1/2 c. biscuit mix in a lrg. bowl.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Stir just until blended.
Knead the dough on a lightly floured surface until well mixed.
Roll into a 1/2 in. thick circle.
Cut with a 2 in. biscuit cutter.
Arrange the biscuits in a 13 by 9 baking pan.
Bake until lightly browned, about 12-15 min.

title: pizza skins
directions: Brush pizza sauce over each wedge.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 425° until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Cream together eggs, oil and sugar.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir all together with zucchini.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Pour into 3 ungreased Teflon-coated loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325° oven.

title: rolls(for 12)
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt and butter; let cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add to milk mixture.
Let stand 15 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Add 2 cups flour; mix until it is smooth. Add enough remaining flour to make nice consistency to knead (not real sticky).
Knead 10 minutes (until elastic) on floured surface.
Cover; let rise in greased bowl until doubled in size. Punch down.
Shape into 12 "balls."
Place on cookie sheet. Cover; let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: sinaloa style grilled chicken
directions: Combine vinegar, water, garlic, salt, chili powder, oregano, pepper and bay leaf. Wash chicken and pat dry. Place chicken in shallow baking dish and marinate. Cover and refrigerate 3 hours, turning once. Bring to room temperature for grilling. Drain from marinade. Cook over hot coals 20 to 30 minutes, basting occasionally. Serve with homemade salsa and tortillas.

title: fiery sweet pork ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving size portions, place in a large dutch oven and cover with water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Drain.
Combine Coca-Cola, soy sauce, black pepper, and garlic powder in a large shallow container.
Add ribs, turning to coat.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator up to 8 hours, turning occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add broccoli, soup, Cheez Whiz, rice and salt.
Bake in buttered dish, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: heath bars
directions: *Do not substitute margarine!

title: graham cracker fruit cake
directions: Mix crushed
crackers,	raisins,
pecans,
cherries and spices in mixing
bowl.
Melt marshmallows in Eagle Brand milk and pour over other ingredients.
Mix as well as you can, then into cracker box lined
with
wax paper and pack cake into it. Store in refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: jan hagel (yahn hahgel)
directions: Lightly grease a jelly roll pan.
Mix butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Blend the flour and cinnamon into the butter mixture.
Pat into the pan and beat the egg white until it's foamy.
Brush it on and sprinkle the nuts on while the egg white is still wet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut while warm and remove from pan. Store in an airtight container when cooled.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls.
Put on a cookie sheet and mash with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Boil eggs first.
Mix sugar with Miracle Whip in second bowl for dressing.
Put lettuce in salad bowl as first layer.
Add green peas as second layer and diced celery as third layer.
Press firmly with hands.
Next, put on bacon, onion, Cheddar cheese and Swiss cheese.
Spread the Miracle Whip mix on top.
Cut up or slice boiled eggs and put on top of salad.
Garnish with red peppers or paprika or green peppers or pimentos.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
(The recipe recommends 24 hours; sometimes there isn't enough time.)

title: chicken bake
directions: Cook onions and peppers in butter until tender.
Stir in soup mushrooms and milk.
Layer half the noodles in 9x13 pan, sprayed with Pam, then layer mixture. Layer cottage cheese, chicken and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until cheese has melted and browned.

title: garlic bread
directions: Cut bread diagonally into 1 inch slices; do not cut all the way through.

title: iced tea
directions: Brew tea bags in boiling water to make very strong tea. Remove tea bags and add sugar to the hot tea.
Stir to dissolve. Pour into large pitcher.
Add lemonade concentrate and enough cold water to make 1/2 gallon.
Chill and serve over ice.

title: recipe secrets vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In bowl, toss vegetables and soup mix with oil.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes or until tender, stirring once.

title: squash casserole
directions: Fry zucchini, onion and green pepper.
While frying, add salt, pepper and garlic salt to first 3 ingredients.

When vegetables are tender, add 4 or 5 eggs (add salt to eggs also) and mix well. Put in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Add grated cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted (about 5 or 10 minutes).

title: japanese chicken wings
directions: Dip chicken in egg and then in flour.
Fry in butter until brown and crisp.
Place in a shallow roasting pan and pour sauce over chicken.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Put cabbage and carrot in a bowl.
Add dressing and shake 1/2 teaspoon celery salt on and mix.
Refrigerate.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel, core and slice tomatoes. Chop onions and peppers. Place in
a large kettle.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on top of the range, stirring
frequently, until the sauce is the consistency of catsup (about 4
hours).
Fill
pint
jars with hot sauce, leaving 1/2 inch
headspace.
Process
in a boiling water bath canner for 15 minutes.
Yields 5 pints.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Mix together in 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole the rice, soups and water.
Season chicken breasts and lay on top of rice mixture. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: tang fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and pineapple.
Mix 1 cup of juice with Tang and pudding.
Then whip.
Fold in fruit and bananas. Put in a 2-quart dish.
Chill and serve.

title: barbecued string beans
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour over string beans, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick low-sugar "cheesecake"
directions: Combine
cracker
crumbs,
sugar
and butter; mix well. Press crumb mixture into an 8-inch pie plate to form crust.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Throw all in blender.
Can be used to marinate any meat or fish.

title: applesauce -- chunky style
directions: In a cooking pot (preferably nonaluminum), combine apples, cider, sugars, rind, juice, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt. Simmer, covered, 15 minutes, stirring once or twice. Uncover and let apples cook until tender. Partially mash, leaving mixture chunky. Let cool, then refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add rice, chicken broth, water and onion soup. Place chicken pieces on rice, skin side up.
Top chicken with undiluted celery soup.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water. Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks and beat. Add chocolate to creamed mixture. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture. Add pecans, coconut and vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter. Pour into ungreased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool for a few minutes and turn out onto cake rack to cool.

title: deluxe spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat.
Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1/2 hour.
Pour sauce over cooked spaghetti.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti as usual.
Drain and mix with 2 tablespoons of butter, the Parmesan and the eggs.
Place in the bottom of a 10-inch greased pie plate.
Spread the cottage cheese over the spaghetti, working the spaghetti up to the sides to form a crust.

title: rainbow salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Cover and chill.
Toss salad before serving.
It's also good with a sprinkling of Parmesan cheese.

title: broccoli stuffed tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice 1/4-inch from stem end of each tomato.
Scoop out pulp and seeds; reserve for another use or discard.
Place in 1-quart glass baking dish.
Cook broccoli with onion according to package directions; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Fill tomatoes with broccoli mixture; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: In a bowl, combine ingredients. Beat with electric mixer on low the first 3 ingredients until fluffy. Fold in Cool Whip until blended. Top with cinnamon and additional Cool Whip, if desired.

title: corn fritters
directions: Cut grains of corn from the cob.
Scrape.
Mash some grains with a potato masher or in a blender.
(This helps to intensify corn flavor.)
Mix egg yolks with corn.
Add flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Beat egg whites, but not dry.
Fold in corn mixture.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix until thoroughly blended.

title: dump cake
directions: In 9 x 11-inch pan, pour pineapple juice and all.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Put dry cake mix on top and spread evenly and put pecans in cake mix.
Cut oleo up evenly over dry cake mix.
Then pour cherry pie filling on top and spread evenly.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Add water to sweet potatoes and salt; cook until almost tender.
Drain and put in greased casserole.
Add brown sugar, cream and flour.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until sticky.
Place small marshmallows on top and brown.

title: braunschweiger ball
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Combine soft braunschweiger with 1/2 carton sour cream, pickle relish, onion soup mix and mayonnaise.
Form into 1 or 2 balls.
Combine softened cream cheese and the remaining sour cream.
Spread over braunschweiger ball.
Sprinkle with ground pecans and garnish with olives.
Chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.
Serves about 25.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together well and baste meat.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: First in a large bowl crush corn flakes with hands. Then add the eggs, salt, baking powder, baking soda, sugar, butter and vanilla. Mix the flour in next then the choc. chips last.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening with brown and white sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; cream well.
Sift flour with soda, salt and baking powder.
Combine oatmeal, rice cereal and coconut.
Fold dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: egg rolls
directions: Chop shrimp in small pieces.
In hot wok, heat 2 tablespoons oil and stir-fry ground pork for 1 minute.
Add mushrooms, celery and shrimp.

Stir-fry for 30 seconds. Add green onions and bean sprouts. Stir in seasonings and cook 30 seconds longer. Thicken with cornstarch if too much liquid. Cool filling before wrapping egg rolls. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons of cool mixture to the bottom edge of egg roll skin.
Roll up and fold sides to seal the mixture. Seal with 1 beaten egg.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Slice in half before serving.

title: apple salad
directions: Melt margarine in oblong dish.
Mix together the sugar and flour.
Stir into margarine until slightly thickened.
Spread crushed pineapple on top of mixture.
Peel and dice apples; spread on top of pineapple.
Top with whipped topping and cover.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Put ribs in broiler pan and broil for about 25 minutes or until browned.
Discard fat.
Cut ribs into serving pieces and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In cooker, alternate layers of ribs, onions and sauerkraut.
Sprinkle with caraway seed and add water.
Cook on low for 7 to 8 hours or on automatic for 3 to 4 hours.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion slices and pepper strips and cook until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook over low heat, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cook shrimp 3 to 5 minutes in boiling water; drain.
Add shrimp to sauce.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: goldfish chex mix
directions: Melt margarine in microwave.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce. Mix together cereals, snacks and peanuts in a large bowl.
Pour butter mixture over top and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Mix well. Spread on cookie sheet and bake 1 hour at 250°, stirring occasionally.

title: yucca flat
directions: Mix all ingredients in very large container.

title: taco casserole
directions: Bake crescent rolls flattened in 9x13 pan. Brown beef and add taco seasoning. Crush bag of Doritos. Place half of Doritos on crescent rolls. Then add meat. Mix sour cream and salsa together and pour over Doritos. Add cheese and remaining Doritos.Bake at 375 degrees for 35-40 minutes. Let sit for 2 minutes. Serve.

title: pineapple cake with icing
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box in 9 x 12-inch pan saving 1 cup cake batter mix.
Cook batter, sugar, oleo and pineapple in double boiler.
As it is easy to scorch, stir while cooking.
Cool to lukewarm and put on warm cake.

title: skim milk mayonnaise(diabetic)
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water; set aside.
Scald milk in top of double boiler.
Slowly pour over beaten eggs, stirring constantly to prevent curdling.
Return egg-milk mixture to the top of the double boiler and add mustard, salt and paprika.
Cook over simmering water, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick enough to coat spoon.
Remove from heat.
Add vinegar, gelatin and artificial sweetener; blend well.
Pour into a pint jar; cover and chill.
Stir before using.

title: coconut easter eggs
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Shape into eggs; dip into chocolate.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except potatoes in order. Peel potatoes and dice while warm. Pour sauce over the warm potatoes and mix thoroughly. Add mayonnaise or salad dressing to taste when ready to serve.

title: minneapolis cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into balls and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: "philly" pound cake
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla, mixing well until blended.
Add eggs; mix on a low speed. Gradually add flour, sifted with baking powder, mixing at low speed, until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet lightly sprayed with nonstick spray.
Press rounds gently with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Cool and enjoy!

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: *Use only sweet onions (Texas 1015, Vidalia).

title: peach crunch
directions: Arrange peaches in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Place 1/4 cup peach syrup over peaches.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly. Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until topping is golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Combine remaining ingredients, except broccoli, melted butter and bread crumbs.
Add broccoli; mix well. Use a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place mixture in dish; top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: minestrone
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Add onion, garlic, carrots, celery and leek.
Saute until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes with liquid, breaking up tomatoes; stir in broth, parsley, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in beans and cabbage.
Simmer 10 minutes longer.
Stir in zucchini and macaroni.
Simmer for 30 minutes and serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: cake doughnuts
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Mix well. Combine remaining ingredients and add to flour mixture, mixing until well blended.
If desired, chill dough for easier handling. Heat
oil
to
Toss
dough
on
well floured surface until no longer sticky.
Roll out half of the dough at a
time to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep hot oil
for 1 to 2 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Drain on
paper
towels.
Shake
a few doughnuts at a time in
a
bag of powdered granulated sugar or cinnamon sugar or dip in your favorite glaze.
Yield:
32 doughnuts.

title: 57 sauce cheddar burgers
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Form into 5 patties. Grill or broil to desired degree of doneness. Serve on buns with additional sauce, if desired.

title: corn and potato scallop
directions: Combine corn, soup, salt and pepper.
Turn into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Dot with butter; sprinkle shredded cheese over top.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked eggs
directions: Generously butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange bread cubes in dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together next 5 ingredients with pepper to taste and pour evenly over cheese and bread. Sprinkle with bacon, mushrooms and tomato. Cover and chill overnight.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake casserole, uncovered, until set, about 1 hour
(tent with foil if top begins to overbrown).
Makes 12 servings.

title: betty's biscuit recipe
directions: Pour small amount of cooking oil in baking pan.
Roll ball of dough in oil.
Make biscuits.
Place in pan.
Bake in 400° oven until brown.

title: potato doughnuts(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Stir in oleo, potatoes and buttermilk. Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to egg mixture and blend well.
Chill for 2 hours.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into rounds with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep hot fat for a few minutes on each side or until light brown.
Drain and dust with sugar.

title: cranberry jello
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Top with 8 ounces softened cream cheese.

title: bobbi's chocolate cookies
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients.
Chill.
Roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: barbecue meat buns
directions: Cook onions in salad oil or melted fat in large skillet over medium
heat
until soft.
Add ground beef and 1 teaspoon of salt. Cook and stir until beef is lightly browned or use 2 1/2
cups chopped
leftover,	cooked	beef,
pork, chicken or turkey instead of
ground beef and do not brown).
Add tomato sauce, prepared mustard, pepper sauce, vinegar and water.
