Let simmer, uncovered, for
10 to 15 minutes.
Serve large spoonfuls on toasted halves of hamburger buns.

title: cottage meat loaf
directions: In large bowl combine ketchup, tomato juice, salt, black and red pepper, eggs, bread crumbs, onions and 2 teaspoons mustard. Mix well.
Add beef, then mix gently.
Line a 9 x 5-inch pan with foil.
Press in beef mixture.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions, celery and mushrooms in margarine and add cooked broccoli, lemon juice and cayenne.
Mix mushroom soup and cheese into broccoli mixture.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted. Serve in a chafing dish.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: nancy croome's baked beans with hamburger meat
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Mix with other ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ground seasoning blend
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in airtight container.
Use in stew, chowder or sandwich spreads.
Yield:
1/4 cup.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, pork, onions and garlic.
Then add tomatoes, tomato sauce, parsley flakes, sugar, salt and basil leaves.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Stir together lemon juice and condensed milk.
Line dish with vanilla wafers.
Layer in order:
bananas, pineapple, milk mixture, Cool Whip, coconut, nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Boil 1 head cauliflower in salt water.
Drain.
Remove to a buttered casserole and season to taste.
Top with butter.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes.
Pour prepared cheese sauce over and serve hot.

title: missouri beef skillet
directions: In skillet, cook ground beef and onions until meat is brown and onions are tender. Drain fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, kidney beans, then water, rice and green peppers.
Add chili powder, salt and garlic; bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Top mixture with cheese and corn chips. Serve when cheese is melted.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Grease a 9 or 10-inch pie plate. Beat all ingredients until smooth or 1 minute in blender.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.

title: vegetable cheesy lemon sauce
directions: Steam vegetables until tender.
Meanwhile, place cream cheese in saucepan.
Cook over heat until softened, stirring constantly. Gradually add half and half, stirring constantly, over low heat until smooth.
Stir in Mrs. Dash and lemon juice.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Butter will melt in warm potatoes.
Pour into baking dish.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Cook sugar and syrup on High 4 minutes.
Add pecans, stir and cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir and add margarine and vanilla, cook 2 minutes.
Add baking soda, stir and pour on a greased cookie sheet.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Crumble crackers.
Melt butter and mix with crackers.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Cook chicken; debone.
Mix broth, soup and vegetables.
Heat.
Add chicken and sour cream.
Pour over crust.
Place biscuits on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: linguine in clam sauce
directions: As you are boiling the water for linguine, melt butter; saute garlic in butter.
Add the clams and some liquid if necessary. Add the fresh parsley.
Simmer.
Pour over the linguine and serve.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake on greased and floured sheet pan, 11 1/2 x 18-inches, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool on rack.
Frost with buttercream frosting.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cajun shrimp and linguine
directions: Saute 1 pound of shrimp pieces in virgin olive oil.
Add oregano, basil and thyme.
In separate pan, fry in olive oil finely chopped onions, green pepper, mushrooms and garlic.
Add cooking wine, tomato sauce and Romano cheese.
Bring to a boil and add 2 cups of cream.
Then add cooked shrimp to mixture.
Cook linguine; cool with water while straining.
Then add ingredients. Add creole seasoning to taste.

title: candied carrots
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan.
Cover and bring to boil, then simmer slowly for about 30 minutes.
Serves 2. This is a Weight Watchers recipe, 1 V, 1/3 Fruit.
One cup equals one serving.
Sweet potatoes may be cooked like this also.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix.
Use approximately 1/3 cup mix in an average cup of hot water.

title: hedda's cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, egg and extract.
Add flour and salt and blend well.
Fold in coconut.
Shape into one-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes until slightly golden around edges. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg whites and fold into cake mixture.
Bake in 3 cake pans, floured and greased.

title: caramels
directions: Add 1 cup of cream with the sugar and syrup and cook it until it forms soft ball in cold water, then add the second cup of cream. Cook until it forms little harder ball in the cold water. Beat creamy; add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into shallow pan and mark in squares while cooling.

title: twinkies
directions: Mix and bake in 2 cookie sheets.

title: tender cube steak
directions: Roll cube steak in flour and salt mixture.
Brown on both sides in shortening; add water to meat and simmer on low until done.
The meat is real tender and makes its own gravy.

title: fruited popcorn
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in airtight container. Makes 12 cups.

title: sweet potato cups
directions: Peel oriental sweet potatoes; cover with water.
Boil and mash.
Add sugar, butter and beaten eggs to the mashed potatoes. Mix well, while potatoes are still hot.
Add milk to the mixture, little by little, mixing well to make a creamy paste.
Put the paste into 12 baking cups (2 1/2 inches).
Gently brush the surface with the mixture of egg yolks and Mirin.
Bake at 480° for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden on top.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Oil cookie sheets well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Combine egg, water and vanilla; set aside.
Blend brown sugar and oil in large bowl at low speed of electric mixer.
Add egg mixture; beat until smooth.
Add flour mixture in 3 parts at lowest speed.
Scrape bowl well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool on cookie sheets for 1 minute. Remove to wire racks.
Each cookie contains 74 calories and 3 grams fat.

title: moon cake
directions: Boil water and margarine together.
Add flour and blend well; cool.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Spread in an ungreased 9 x 13-inch glass dish, jelly roll pan or pizza pan. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Prepare the pudding as directed on the box.
Add cream cheese and beat well.
Spread over the cream puff base.
Cover with prepared whipped topping; drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: skillet cookies
directions: In a heavy saucepan or cast-iron skillet, mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and cook over medium heat for 12 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly and add vanilla, nuts and Rice Krispies.
Spread on cookie sheet and slice.
These can also be shaped into balls the size of a walnut and roll in coconut.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil in a large bowl.
Stir to mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well into the sugar and oil.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add this mixture to the oil mixture.
Stir well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Spoon batter into a well-greased 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Place lettuce and romaine in plastic bag; add celery and onions.
Pour Sweet-Sour Dressing into bag; add orange segments. Close bag tightly and shake until all of the contents are coated. Add almonds and shake.

title: awesome chocolate chip cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Roll out cookie dough into a 8- inch pan.
Scatter chopped pecans over cookie.
Scatter chocolate chip morsels over pecans.
Slice candy bars and place on top. Bake for 25-30 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: hawaii pie
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients until thickened.
Cool.
Place bananas on bottom of pie shell.
Pour in mixture.
Add coconut. Put whipped cream on top.

title: green bean with mushroom soup
directions: Drain 1 can of beans and use liquid in other can to heat beans and red pepper.
When heated thoroughly, add mushroom soup.

title: turkey or ham tetrazzini
directions: Saute the onions in the butter or margarine, adding the mushrooms as well.
Add seasonings, blend in the broth, stirring until smooth. Gradually add the milk, stirring until smooth and somewhat thickened.
Meanwhile, cook and drain the spaghetti.
In a buttered, shallow casserole, mix the cooked turkey pieces with the spaghetti.
Pour the sauce over, blending together.
Top with the cheeses, and bake at 350° for half an hour, just until the top is lightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat
eggs
on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar. Stir
in
pumpkin	and
lemon
juice.
Set aside.	Mix together flour,
baking
powder,
pumpkin pie spice and salt. Fold into egg
mixture.
Grease
a
jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch) and line with wax paper.
Spread dough onto pan.
Chop 1/2 cup	nuts and
sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: bread spreads
directions: Soften cream cheese. Blend all together until of spreading consistency.

title: crab paste
directions: Clean shrimp.
Cook with salt and pepper by bringing to boil and let sit in
hot
water
for 3 to 4 minutes.
Grind in meat grinder or
process in food processor, the shrimp, celery and onion.
Add
other
ingredients.
Chill
hours.
Great served on crackers or sandwiches.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Cream together cream cheese, Hidden Valley dressing and Miracle Whip until smooth, then spread on baked cool crust.
Chop the vegetables and spread evenly over the cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate until set.
Cut into serving size pieces.

title: corn, okra and tomatoes
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine and saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Add okra, water and tomatoes.
Cook on medium heat, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add more water as needed as cooking progresses.
Stir in corn and Tabasco.
Continue to cook on simmer for 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste, then cook, uncovered, for another 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute
cup
chopped
onion in 1/2 stick oleo until soft. Add
cup raw rice;
stir and add 1 can beef consomme and mushrooms.	Add 1/2 can water.
Pinch of curry is optional.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well; turn in greased loaf pan and let rise 20 to 25 minutes.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
After it cools, break it up into medium size pieces.
Pour Kahlua over top and let it soak 3 to 6 hours.
Make mousse mix but do not refrigerate.
Break Skor bars up by hand.
Put into bowl by layers (cake, mousse, Skor and Cool Whip).
Continue to layer until all ingredients have been used.

title: putsch's spinach salad
directions: Stem, wash and dry spinach.
Refrigerate.
Tear spinach into small pieces, then chop finely.
Sprinkle with salt.
Blend vinegar and Tabasco and mix with spinach.
Add celery, onion, chopped eggs and cheese.
Blend in mayonnaise and stir until well coated.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Garnish with one tablespoon shredded egg.
Place 2 tablespoons horseradish on the side.

title: aunt florence's baked beans
directions: Cook beans until tender, then add rest of ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Crush graham crackers and add butter.
Pat in bottom of dessert dishes.
Melt together marshmallows and milk.
Cool, then fold in whipped cream and blueberries.
Cool Whip or other nondairy whipped topping can be used instead of whipped cream.
Chill and serve.

title: easy beef and noodle stroganoff
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Microwave Cheez Whiz according to label directions.
Stir in 1/2 jar Cheez Whiz and seasonings to meat mixture.
Arrange hot noodles on serving platter; top with ground beef mixture and remaining Cheez Whiz.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time:
15 minutes.

title: funnel cake mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield:
1 cup (enough for 6 funnel cakes).

title: challah(jewish sabbath bread)
directions: Combine 2 cups water, yeast and sugar in small bowl; set aside to rise.
Combine 9 cups flour, salt, eggs and oil in large mixing bowl.
Add yeast mixture and 1 cup water.
Mix well.
Sprinkle 1 cup flour on board; turn out dough and knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise in warm place until double in size (about an hour).
Turn out on floured surface.
Punch down and divide in half.
Divide each half into 3 equal parts and form into 15-inch lengths.
Place 3 lengths on a greased baking sheet and braid.
Repeat with other lengths.
Press ends together and turn under.
Cover; let rise 45 minutes.
Brush with combined egg yolk and water.
Sprinkle with sesame or poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: cauliflower scallop
directions: Combine soup, milk and eggs.
Stir in 1/2 of the cheese, the bread crumbs, parsley, pimiento, onion, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Chop cauliflower.
Stir into soup mixture.

title: mom's applesauce cake
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish while oven is preheating.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add the brown sugar and applesauce to the melted margarine and mix well.
Add the dry ingredients to the applesauce mixture.
Stir with fork to mix well.
Stir in vanilla. Add nuts and raisins, if desired.
Mix and smooth entire surface. Bake 40 minutes for plain cake and 50 to 55 minutes with nuts and raisins.
When cool, dust with sifted powdered sugar or serve with Cool Whip.

title: carrot-rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole. Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and roll into bite size meatballs. Cook in a 325° oven until cooked through. Combine ingredients except beans in soup pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes. Stir often.
Add beans.
Heat through.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix together and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Grease a Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from pan and split cake into 2 layers.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Generously grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom of pan.
Thoroughly combine berries and dry gelatin.
Set aside.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a bowl. Blend at low speed until moistened, 3 minutes at medium speed. Pour batter evenly into pan.
Spoon berry mixture over batter. Bake in 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with Cool Whip, ice cream or whipped cream.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish that will be used for baking the noodle pudding.
Cook noodles.
Beat eggs until frothy; add eggs to noodles in casserole dish.
Add the rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs on top.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Combine chicken, water, salt and peppercorns in a large saucepan.
Cover.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours until chicken is tender. Remove chicken and peppercorns.
Skim off fat.
Cut chicken into small cubes.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients to broth. Cover; simmer 30 minutes until rice is tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashion chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender; remove the bones. Salt chicken. Put in pan and pepper to taste. Make biscuit dough. Roll out and place a layer in pan. Cook in oven until done.
Repeat another layer and put back in oven. Cook until brown. Take out of oven and put on top of stove. Add sweet milk and simmer until it thickens. Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Combine oats, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix in milk, egg and oil, stirring gently until just moist. Fold in blueberries. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full with batter. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: mini cheese blintzes
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Mix together egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Spread cream cheese mixture on bread slices. Roll slices jelly roll fashion and cut into thirds.
Continue this process until all bread is used.
Melt margarine, combine remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Roll cream cheese filled bread in melted margarine and then in sugar cinnamon mixture.
Freeze until needed.
Bake frozen blintzes at 350° for 13 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Heat butter and half and half in 1-quart saucepan until butter is melted. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Keep warm over low heat.
Pour sauce over hot noodles, stirring gently until noodles are well coated.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix with beaten eggs, soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Place in a buttered casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar when ready to serve.

title: chicken kelly
directions: Marinate chicken in beaten eggs for 2 hours.
Put seasoned crumbs in bag and shake chicken pieces until coated.
Brown in oil and drain on paper towels.
Use covered casserole dish.
Layer of chicken, layer of grated cheese.
Pour bouillon over.
Put margarine in pieces on top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pink lady punch
directions: Mix juices and sugar; add ginger ale just before serving. Serves 32.

title: pto's baked beans with beef
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Combine the beef and the beans in a large dish. Mix remaining ingredients. In the baking dish, combine the beef and beans and mix together with the ketchup mixture. Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: summer chicken salad
directions: On salad plates, arrange spinach leaves, chicken, fruit, celery, almond and green onion.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine in frying pan and saute rice, onion, pepper and butter.
In large bowl, combine water or milk, soup and seasonings. Combine rice and liquid mixture and pour all into a large casserole dish.
Place 1/2 chicken, cut in serving size pieces on top.
Bake covered for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Stir occasionally to check for rice drying.

title: fried frozen corn
directions: Place both in frying pan and cover. Fry on medium setting. Watch carefully and stir often.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, mix zucchini, sugar, eggs and salad oil.
Then combine dry ingredients; stir into the zucchini mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Place in greased bread pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate spice cake (small)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add egg and sifted dry ingredients. Add buttermilk and baking soda.
Bake in 7x7-inch pan for 35-40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: vegetable rice
directions: In medium saucepan, bring water and bouillon to a boil.
Add rice. Bring back to boiling and simmer until done.
(If using Minute rice, follow directions on package.)

title: baked persimmon pudding
directions: Mix the persimmon pulp, beaten eggs and milk.
Sift the dry ingredients together and pour the liquid mixture into them.
Stir in melted margarine.
Pour into shallow greased pan to the depth of about 2-inches.
Bake for about 1 hour in a very moderate oven (300° to 325°).
When cold, cut into squares and serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: rotel chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; reserve broth. Boil spaghetti in broth. Cook pepper and onion in oleo until tender. Mix all ingredients in baking dish. Cover and cook at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes, until bubbly.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix meat, onion, corn, sauce, water and seasoning; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix dry ingredients with oil, then add crackers and stir until the crackers are coated.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate pie(easy)
directions: Mix ingredients; cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture thickens and comes to full boil.
Cool 5 minutes and put in 8-inch or 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: green rice
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend thoroughly. Bake in greased baking dish at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tasty nut granola
directions: Heat oats in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Combine oats, sesame seed, wheat germ, coconut, nuts and sugar.
Add oil, honey and vanilla.
Mix until dry ingredients are well coated.
Bake half in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°, stirring often.
Repeat for other half.
Stir until crumbly.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Chop candied cherries and pineapple fine and mix with part of flour. Mix well and bake in 2 greased loaf pans (4 1/2 x 9-inch) at 275° for 1 1/2 hours or until turns loose from pan.

title: easy mix sugar cookies
directions: Stir together sugar, oil and egg.
Stir in dry ingredients. Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Use 1 tablespoon of dough. Roll into ball and place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Flatten with juice glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Beat together egg yolks, lemon juice and rind and butter until thick and lemon colored.
Combine sugar, flour and salt and add to egg mixture alternately with milk, beating after each addition. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Blend into batter, using low speed of beater.
Pour into an 8-inch square baking dish and set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with Cool Whip.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tangy barbecue chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, sesame oil, garlic, onions and ginger in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil to dissolve sugar and stir to blend flavors. Cool and pour over chicken.
Let stand at room temperature for 2 hours or refrigerate for 4 hours.
Bring chicken back to room temperature.
Place on grill and grill each side for 10 minutes.
Brown remaining sauce on chicken while on grill.

title: sauerkraut & lima beans
directions: Put beans and ribs in a large pan.
Cover with water and cook on low heat for 3 hours or more.
Add sauerkraut and onion.
Cook 1/2 hour longer.
Note:
Before adding sauerkraut and onion, cool overnight and skim fat.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs in bowl until fluffy.
Add sugar and vanilla and blend well. Stir in zucchini.
Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder together.
Add this to sugar and egg mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Put in prepared pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until bread tests done.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Let butter soften.
Cream with sugar.
Add egg yolks, two at a time.
Alternate dry ingredients with sour cream until all are mixed.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Fold in by hand.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Can be baked in a Bundt or an angel food pan.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies into crumbs and mix with 1/2 cup margarine, melted.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Oreo mixture.
Spread the softened ice cream over the cookie mixture.
Freeze until almost set.
Sprinkle the peanuts over the ice cream.
Freeze until firm.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg with hand beater until fluffy; beat in remaining ingredients just until smooth.
For thinner pancakes, stir in additional 1/4 cup milk.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Step 1: Mix cake mix as per directions on box. Bake as usual. Make holes in cake with fork while hot.

title: skillet coffee cake
directions: Melt butter and add to sugar in mixing bowl.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt and flavoring and mix well.
Line a 9 to 11-inch iron skillet with aluminum foil.
Leave excess foil on either side.
Pour batter into skillet.
Sprinkle almonds and granulated sugar on top of batter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove cake from pan after it has cooled with foil; lift out, holding excess foil.
Do not pull foil off until cake has cooled.

title: "ala" clam chowder
directions: Drain clams; reserve liquid.
Cook celery and onion in butter until tender.
Stir in peas and potatoes, chicken soup, water, milk, clam liquid, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until mixture bubbles.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in clams and heat to boiling.
Garnish with paprika.

title: healthy vegetable soup
directions: Mix together in pan.
Bring to a boil and let simmer for several hours.

title: stone soup
directions: Bring water to a boil; add whole tomatoes and bring back to boiling.
Add onion, rice, bouillon cubes, potatoes, garlic powder and hamburger meat (crumbled).
Boil 45 minutes.
Add canned goods.
Season to taste.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Skin and slice.
Combine rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil and boil 10 minutes.
Pack beets in sterile jars. Pour boiling syrup to cover.
Seal.
Makes about 4 quarts or 8 pints.

title: caramel pecans
directions: Beat
egg
white
stiff.
Fold in brown sugar.	Stir in pecan halves.
Take each pecan half and place on cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: flaming bananas over ice cream
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add bananas; sprinkle in coconut mixture.
Add 2 tablespoons rum.
Cook until bananas are tender (about 3 minutes). Tilt skillet.
Add rest of rum.
Heat slightly and ignite.
When flames subside, spoon bananas over ice cream.

title: easy cream puffs
directions: Let water, butter and salt come to a boil, then add 1 cup flour and stir well into a ball.
Let cool, then add 4 eggs one at a time.
Beat 5 minutes for each egg.
Drop by tablespoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Reduce to 325° for 20 minutes longer.
When cool, split open and fill with cream filling.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: quick fudge
directions: Heat chips and milk, stirring until melted.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Chill 4 hours.

title: good luck black-eyed peas
directions: Fry bacon and ham until slightly brown.
Add onion and saute about 15 minutes.
Add green pepper and saute about 10 minutes. Pour in black-eyed peas with liquid and simmer for 1 hour.
Cover for the last 15 minutes.
I use my leftover ham from Christmas and always serve this on New Year's Day for good luck!

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to sugar, oil and egg mixture. Add carrots and nuts last.
Bake in greased, floured tube cake pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut bars
directions: Melt margarine and add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and add to mixture.
Add coconut. Spread into greased (or sprayed with Pam) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until it just begins to turn golden.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk and set aside to thicken.
Start with wafers, then strawberries, then pudding and make layers (2 of each).
Top with Cool Whip.

title: company casserole
directions: Put all in a casserole, cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Stir and cook.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by spoonful in hot oil. Brown on both sides and drain on paper towel.

title: chocolate chip cookies #1
directions: Mix together eggs, shortening, oil, sugars and vanilla. Stir in
flour,
salt,
baking soda, nuts and chocolate chips. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 11 x 15-inch pan with Pam cooking spray.
In pan, spread thin layer of coconut.
Next spread a thin layer of pecans.
Make cake mix batter according to package directions.
Pour on top of layers of coconut and pecans.
Do not stir.
Blend cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Drop blobs all over the top of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake for 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted between blobs comes out clean.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Melt butter.
Mix drained crabmeat with other ingredients. Spread on English muffin; split, top and bottom.
Place on cookie sheet for 6 to 8 minutes.
Broil.
Remove; cut into quarters.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Blend ingredients until smooth, then you add 3/4 cup more oil in a steady stream until it is all mixed in.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp in a saucepan.
Simmer 5 minutes. Add cooked shrimp.
Simmer just until heated.
Serve over cooked rice.
Makes about 3 servings.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth, about 1 minute.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla extract. Beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate morsels.

title: ranchero dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and whisk until smooth.
Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine chicken, celery, cooked rice, Miracle Whip, chopped onion, lemon juice, salt, pepper, water chestnuts, cream of chicken soup, chopped boiled eggs and water.
Place in 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/4 cup butter.
Add bread crumbs and Cheddar cheese.
Toss.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with almonds that have already been toasted with a little margarine in the oven.
Return to oven and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: gouda meat loaf
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Form around Gouda cheese.
Mix together catsup and vinegar and pour over meat loaf. Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Let rest a few minutes before serving.

title: old pecan street special
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in chopped pecans and pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: veggie bake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients. Place in a baking dish and crumble crackers on top. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: easy pizza
directions: Spread muffin with 2 teaspoons pizza sauce, 1 1/2 tablespoons cooked ground beef and 1
1/2 tablespoons cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Spray muffin pans with vegetable shortening.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Batter can be kept in the refrigerator up to 6 weeks and cooked as needed.

title: spiced oyster cracker snacks
directions: Combine dry Ranch mix and oil.
Add spices and stir well. Pour over crackers in a bowl; stir to coat all crackers.
Place in warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir around several times during baking time.
Store covered.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Excellent dip for cut up apples, other fruit or crackers.

title: potluck potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns and combine in big bowl with melted margarine.
Add salt, pepper, onion and soups to sour cream. Blend thoroughly and pour into buttered 3-quart casserole dish. Melt 1/4 cup butter and pour on cornflakes.
Spread over top of other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: skillet casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Leave it in the skillet.
Add rice, drained sauerkraut, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce over all ingredients.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: peppermint bark
directions: Melt bark according to package directions.
Crush candy with a toffee hammer or rolling pin while it is enclosed in a heavyweight Ziploc bag.
Stir crushed candy into melted bark.
Spread into a thin layer on waxed paper.
Let cool and break into bite-sized pieces.

title: old fashioned chocolate angel food cake
directions: Light oven at 375°.
Sift flour and measure.
Add 3/4 cup sugar and sift 4 times.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy. Sprinkle in cream of tartar; beat until stiff enough to hold up in soft peaks.
Add remaining 1 1/3 cups sugar in 4 additions; fold in each addition, turning bowl.
Use 15 complete strokes.
After last addition, use 10 to 24 strokes.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: fiesta grilled avocados
directions: Place olive oil in a small bowl.
Dip Avocado halves in olive oil.
Sprinkle avocados with fajita seasoning and place on a sheet pan.
Heat coals or grill to medium heat, 375 degrees.
Brush hot grill with olive oil to prevent sticking.
Grill chicken breasts according to package directions and thin slice.
Grill avocados on cut side for 5 minutes.
Turn avocados over and grill for 3 minutes.
Place grilled avocados on a small foil lined baking pan and top with sliced chicken, salsa and shredded cheese.
Place pan on grill and loosely cover with foil.
Heat avocados for 3 more minutes until cheese melts.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice; saute onions and celery in margarine until onions are clear.
Cook broccoli; then drain.
Combine all ingredients; put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook milk and rice 1 hour in a double boiler.
Add salt and most of the sugar and cook 5 more minutes.
Add vanilla and stir. Remove from heat and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar and some cinnamon.
Put a couple drops of butter on top.

title: fudge
directions: Heat sugar and milk to a rolling boil. Stir constantly and boil 6 minutes. Remove from heat and add rest of ingredients. Stir until butter and chips are melted and blended.
Pour in 13 x 9 pan. Refrigerate until firm. Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat in butter or margarine.
Add garlic powder and broth.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add onions and peppers. Cook 5 more minutes.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce. Cook, stirring, until thickened.
(May be served over rice.)

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Beat in sugar and oil.
Add cocoa, vanilla and zucchini.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon
and soda.
Add to mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Mix well.
Makes 2 small loaves.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pans 15 to 20 minutes. Turn out on rack to cool.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: In a double boiler, melt a roll of jalapeno cheese with a can of chili with beans.
Serve with corn chips.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs with corn kernels.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to corn mixture.
Stir in melted margarine and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole or baking dish.
Place casserole in a large pan of hot water. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: spicy apple cake
directions: *Plump raisins in hot water, then drain liquid off.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: black olive casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and set aside.
Brown meat.
Add onion, olives and tomatoes.
Cook for a few minutes.
Add cooked macaroni.
Mix well.
Add grated cheeses on top.
Cook in oven to melt cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bone after cooking.
Stir in cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: apple crunch
directions: Mix together and bake at 350°.
Serve with caramel sauce or Cool Whip.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Pour beans in a bowl and mash in juice.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300°.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, evaporated milk and butter or oleo to soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat and add chocolate bits, Marshmallow fluff, vanilla and walnut meats. Heat until chocolate bits are melted and well blended. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and cut.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in an 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter.
Arrange pineapple on butter-sugar mixture.
Decorate with cherries, if desired.
Stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in mixture in mixer bowl.
Add shortening, milk and flavoring; beat 2 minutes at medium speed or 300 vigorous strokes by hand.
Add egg.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.
Immediately turn upside down on serving plate.
Yields 8 servings.

title: dark cherry salad
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Combine fruit juice and wine and add enough water to make amount of liquid needed per jello pkg instructions.
Combine liquid mixture to fruit and dry jello mixture, mix until jello dissolves, let set up in refrigerator.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan.
Mix sugar and margarine.
Stir in bananas and eggs until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cereal.
Stir in cereal.
Spread in pan.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Grease 12 (3 x 1 1/4-inch) muffin cups or line with paper liners.

title: chocolate chip sandies
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter on medium speed for 30 seconds. Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add water and vanilla; beat well. Stir in flour, half of the chocolate pieces and the pecans.
Shape dough into 1 1/2 x 1/2-inch crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: stuffed french bread
directions: Slice loaf in half lengthwise; scoop out
some	of
the bread from the middle.
Combine the next	4 ingredients; spoon into bread.
Top
with	crab-mayonnaise
mixture.
Sprinkle paprika and parsley on top for color.
Bake at
for
20 minutes.

title: date nut torte
directions: Beat eggs.
Beat in 1 cup sugar.
Mix fine bread crumbs and baking powder.
Stir into egg and sugar mixture.
Stir in dates (finely cut and finely sprinkled with sugar to keep from sticking) and walnuts.
Spread in well-greased (or Pam sprayed) 9-inch square pan.
Bake until set at 350° about 35 minutes.
Serve plain, frosted or with ice cream.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots in a large bowl.
Add salt.
Stir in mayonnaise until creamy.
Add more mayonnaise if needed for taste.

title: freeze and bake rolls
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in water.
Add 2 teaspoons sugar; let stand for 5 minutes.
Add milk, oil, salt and remaining sugar.
Add enough flour to form stiff dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch down.
Divide into 4 pieces.
Cover three pieces with plastic wrap.
Divide one piece into 12 balls.

title: blueberry cake roll
directions: Mix first four ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool in refrigerator.
Mix next four ingredients and pour over other mixture and chill. Top with 1 cup blueberry or cherry pie filling.
Serve in squares.

title: tuna salad
directions: Flake tuna and dice eggs; mix.
Add mayonnaise, pickle relish and seasonings.
May serve chilled or right away.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour in greased and floured baking dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; set aside.
Melt shortening; let cool. Add 1 tablespoon hot water.
Stir in egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Rub large wooden salad bowl with cut clove of garlic.
Allow a few small pieces of garlic to remain in bowl, if desired.
Mix oil, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt, mustard and pepper in bowl.
Add romaine and toss until leaves are coated.
Sprinkle with croutons and cheese; toss.
Makes 6 servings, 180 calories per serving.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Slice potatoes and onions thin in a 2-quart casserole dish. Pour the soup over layered vegetables.
Season and top with a layer of uncooked ground beef.
Cover the casserole with foil and cook until vegetables are tender.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Toss ingredients together.
Bake in a greased baking dish for 1 hour at 350°.

title: clam chowder
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Drain.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Add water to liquid to equal 1 3/4 cups. Cover clams and chill.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in a greased baking dish.

title: barbeque spareribs
directions: Place ribs in glass baking dish and cover with onion slices. Cover with wax paper and microwave at 40% power for 25 minutes. Turn ribs and rearrange.
Combine remaining ingredients and brush over ribs.
Microwave 20 minutes at 40% power.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Set aside. Cream butter and shortening together. Add sugar. Beat well. Add egg yolks. Beat well. Combine flour and soda together; sift 3 times. Add flour mixture and buttermilk alternately to batter. Add vanilla, coconut and chopped nuts. Fold in egg whites, then pour into three 9-inch pans, greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pork and rice simplicity
directions: Put pork chops in baking dish, then put 1 cup rice.
Then pour 2 cups water and also the onion soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: holly's spinach balls
directions: Strain spinach.
Mix in rest of ingredients.
Roll into balls. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Mix apples, cinnamon and cloves and put in an 8 x 8-inch pan. In a separate bowl, mix quick oats, brown sugar, melted butter, flour and nuts.
Crumble the mixture on top
of the apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Boil chicken and reserve broth.
In a soup pot, brown sausage in oil.
Add onions.
Cook until wilted.
Dice chicken and add to sausage mixture.
Add roux, broth, salt, pepper and as much water as desired.
Simmer on low heat for 2 hours.
If desired, add whole eggs to gumbo.
They will boil and absorb the flavor.
You can peel and eat them alone or diced up in your gumbo.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients, then press mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands and run through star shaped cookie press.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Combine 1/4 cup soup with remaining ingredients (except water).
Mix and shape into 6 patties and place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Combine remaining soup with water and pour over patties.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more until hot.
Great served with noodles.
Serves 6.

title: bread in a jar
directions: Grease insides of 6 wide-mouth canning jars (1 pint size), but not the rims.
Place on baking sheet.
Cream the sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs and water.
Add fruit.
Sift flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Add to batter. If desired, add raisins and/or nuts.
Put 1 cup of batter into each jar (no more).
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven; wipe rims.
Cover with hot, flat canning lids and screw tightly.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Measure corn syrup and sugar into large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until sugar dissolves and mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: jello salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Make jello; omit 1 cup of water.
Soft set jello.
Mix cream cheese, celery, carrots and nuts.
Mix well. Stir into Cool Whip, then fold into soft set jello.
Chill until firm.

title: cooking commercial dry pudding mix
directions: Empty pudding mix into 1-quart glass measure.
Add 1/2 cup milk and stir until all mix is moistened and blended.
Add 1 1/2 cups more milk and blend well.
Microwave at High 6 to 8 minutes, stirring thoroughly every 3 minutes.
Pour into 4 or 5 serving dishes or prepared pie crust. Cover top of pudding with wax paper or plastic wrap to prevent "skin" from forming on top.
Chill and serve.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: sweet and sour meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar and mustard in a small bowl until blended.
Place the remaining ingredients and 1 cup of the sauce mixture in a large bowl.
Blend thoroughly.

title: one dish chicken
directions: Stir stuffing mix, 1/2 cup hot water and 1/4 cup margarine (cut in small pieces) just until moistened.
Place chicken in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: peach bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add the peaches, margarine and egg.
Fold in nuts or raisins.
Pour in loaf pan (greased and floured).
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on wire rack.
Freezes well and tastes best when sliced the day after baking.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip with yogurt and blend well.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: layered cookie dessert
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
Crush cookies and set aside.
Melt margarine in large bowl and add sugar.
Mix with cookies.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs.
Sift flour with baking powder, spices and salt. Add to creamed mixture, then add raisins and potatoes.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean when tested, about 35 minutes.
Use loaf pans.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix corn bread according to directions.
Add with cheese, chilies and pimentos.
Bake according to package directions.
Let cool.
In large bowl, crumble corn bread.
Add remaining ingredients.
Use enough mayonnaise for moisture.
Serve cold!

title: low-fat banana cream pie
directions: Blend pudding mix with 1 cup skim milk.
Put 1/3 of pudding into graham cracker crust.
Slice bananas over top of pudding. Add balance of pudding mix, then top with Cool Whip.
Chill before serving.

title: tetrazzini
directions: In a pan, cook onion in margarine.
Blend in soup, water and 1/2 cup of cheese. Cook to melt cheese.
Add chicken, etc., and put in a 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and breading meal. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Stir together in slow cooker the night before and set at 300° or low heat.
It's ready in the morning to go for potluck.
Or you can bake in the oven at 450° for 1 1/2 hours for the same day.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion until tender in hot oil.
Combine soup and milk and stir into celery/onion mixture.
Stir in cheese, broccoli and rice until cheese is melted.
Pour into 10 x 6-inch baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated throughout.

title: easy chocolate chip torte
directions: In the bottom of a 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan, place 10 to 12 cookies in one layer.
Crumble 3 to 5 cookies to fill in the spaces, using a total of 15 cookies.

title: jezebel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and heat until melted.
Cool to room temperature.
Serve with ham cubes, sausage balls, pork bits on toothpicks or punch holes in cream cheese and pour sauce over cheese and serve with Triscuits.
This can be stored indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until it's creamy.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar and beat well.
Gradually stir about 1 cup milk into yolk mixture.
Add to remaining milk, stirring constantly.
Pour into top of a double boiler.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat, stir constantly, until it reaches the thickness you want.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sour cream loaf cake
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl, mix the sour cream, sugar and eggs; add to dry ingredients alternately with 1/4 cup milk.
Add nutmeg and/or vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: best broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion in margarine and put in casserole dish.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz and mix until smooth.
Cook rice according to package directions.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Cook the broccoli just slightly before adding to the casserole.
Put seasoned bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top for the last 5 or 10 minutes.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Spread 1 cup Cool Whip in bottom of pie crust; freeze for 10 minutes.
Carefully spoon jam over Cool Whip.
Gradually add milk to peanut butter in bowl, blending until smooth.
Add pudding mix. With electric mixer at low speed, beat until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in remaining Cool Whip.
Spoon over jam in pie crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with additional Cool Whip and chopped nuts before serving, if desired.

title: chicken or turkey crunch casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, eggs, mushrooms, celery, almonds and onion.
Stir soup into mayonnaise; toss with chicken mixture.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with noodles.
Bake 30 minutes or until mixture is bubbling at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: california medley
directions: Microwave vegetables to thaw and warm.
Spread in greased Pyrex dish.
Slice cheese and cover top of vegetables.
Mix crushed crackers in enough butter to coat well.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ida cecil's cake layers
directions: Sift or blend together flour and sugar.
Add shortening and 1 cup of milk.
Mix to blend.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add remaining milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Cook at 375°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spread raw rice, sprinkled with salt, in 9 x 12 x 14-inch baking dish.
Place browned pork chops over rice.
On each pork chop, place slice of onion, slice of tomato and ring of bell pepper.
Pour 2 cans of consomme over this.
Seal well with tinfoil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: seasoned potatoes(club member: terah smith)
directions: Melt butter in large skillet. Slice potatoes thin; add potatoes to butter. Add chopped bell pepper, onion and Season-All salt. Simmer for 15 minutes over low heat.

title: bacon cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Chill before serving. Great served with Town House crackers.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: Open the cake mix and follow the package directions for the cake. Pour into a greased cookie sheet (the kind with sides) or a jelly roll pan. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Allow to cool.

title: uncle dick's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and baste on hamburgers or chicken or ribs.

title: janie's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the powdered
sugar,
granulated sugar and margarine. Add oil, eggs
and	vanilla; mix together.	Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Make small balls; place on cookie sheet. Press with bottom of a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: garlic potatoes for two
directions: Place potatoes, garlic and salt in small saucepan.
Add water to cover and bring to boil.
Cover pan loosely and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain, reserving potatoes and garlic. Remove garlic and crush with flat side of knife.
Combine garlic with butter and green onion.
Add to potatoes, tossing lightly to coat.

title: apple crisp cake
directions: Pour apples in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle sugar over apples. Sprinkle some apple spice or cinnamon to taste. Evenly sprinkle cake mix over apple mixture. Slice the margarine on top of cake mix. Bake at 350° until done.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in an air-tight container.
To make a mug of hot chocolate, add 1/2 cup of mix to hot water and stir.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Remove wing tips and cut each wing into two pieces.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over the wings.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste every 30 minutes.

title: sourdough pancakes for 4 to 5
directions: Combine water, milk, Starter and flour.
Blend together and take out new Starter.
Let stand at room temperature overnight. Next morning, add eggs, sugar, salt, soda and oil.
Mix well.
Cook on griddle at moderate heat (375°).

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Add pumpkin and beat well. Add milk.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: corned beef and potato casserole
directions: Chop corned beef coarsely; place in a 6-cup casserole.
Add mustard, caraway seed, salt and pepper; toss to mix well.
Dot top with butter.
Stir in potato and onion mix; pour water over.
Stir with a fork; cover.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes, stirring once after 10 minutes.
Uncover; stir with a fork.
Place tomato slices, overlapping, in a ring around edge of casserole.
Continue baking 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rhea's surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the cake mix, sugar, water and oil. Add the vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Fold in the sour cream. Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Mix the brown sugar, oleo and cinnamon.
Add the nuts.
Spoon on top of the batter.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes.
Turn out right away; cool.
Pour a thin powdered sugar glaze over the cake while it is warm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over medium heat to soft ball stage on candy thermometer.
Add the next 3 ingredients (1/2 stick butter, peanut butter and marshmallows).
Boil until starts to thicken and pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan and cook according to the directions.
Cream the cheese with sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cooled cookie dough.
Top with fruit!

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients as listed.
Cook peas and cool.
Mix together mayonnaise and sugar; spread over layers.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: sugar-free coconut pie
directions: Mix together and spread in Pyrex dish and cook until brown; let cool.

title: cookie sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Beat butter and 1/4 cup powdered sugar until light and creamy.
Mix in water and vanilla.
Add flour slowly, beating well after each addition.
Mix in salt.
Stir in pecans.
Form 1-inch balls using your hands.
Bake on greased cookie sheet about 40 minutes.
When done, roll in powdered sugar and coat.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add last remaining ingredients to mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: top of the stove tuna and noodles
directions: Cook
noodles
nearly
done.
Drain tuna and mushrooms. Add to noodles;
drain
off all but about 1/2 cup liquid from noodles. Mix
tuna
and
mushrooms thoroughly.
Add cheese in strips and let melt down; stir slightly and serve.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Saute garlic in butter and add rest; cook until shrimp are pink.
Toss in spaghetti.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: strawberry margarita pie
directions: Mix pretzels,
sugar and butter in 9-inch pie plate. Press mixture onto bottom and up side of pie plate. Refrigerate until ready to fill.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine vegetables, soup, half of the Swiss cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento and half can of the onions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining Swiss cheese and onions; bake uncovered for 5 minutes longer, until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and sausage casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook down tomatoes until there are about 2 cups liquid; stir in sugar.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper. Heat oil in large skillet and add chicken pieces.
Prick sausages with fork and add.
Saute them both until browned on all sides, about 15 minutes.
Pour off all fat.
Scatter the onions, mushrooms, garlic and peppers in between pieces of chicken and sausage.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Add tomatoes, broth and red wine; stir to loosen brown bits in skillet.
Cover tightly and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: viennese raspberry squares
directions: Bring egg whites to room temperature; set aside.

title: cheese and sausage bake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread over a large baking dish and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until sausage is done.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat shortening, sugar and egg until creamy. Mix the cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves with the flour.
Mix the baking soda with the applesauce.
Add the flour mixture alternately with the applesauce to the creamed mixture.
Fold in the raisins.
Turn into a greased and floured 11 1/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Can also be baked in a loaf (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pan, allow longer baking time.

title: easy refrigerator pickles
directions: Place half of cucumbers in a large bowl; top with half of onions.
Repeat layers with remaining cucumbers and onions.

title: buckeyes
directions: In a bowl mix sugar, margarine and peanut butter; knead like dough and form into balls.
Try to size them to look like buckeyes.
Place on a cookie sheet and put in refrigerator until solid, or place in freezer for a few minutes.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Use toothpicks to dip each ball in chocolate.
Place on waxed pepper on a cookie sheet until firm.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Makes 5 cups.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove bones and oil from salmon.
Add ingredients.
Grease top of double boiler and steam for 1 hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together celery soup and softened cream cheese.
Layer each vegetable; pour soup and cheese mixture on.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut fresh tomatoes into wedges and place on top of casserole.

title: strawberry lemon punch
directions: Dissolve
lemonade
with 4 cans of
cold
water.
Puree strawberries, one bag at a time, in a blender
or food processor. Strain to remove seeds.
Blend with sugar
and stir into lemonade. Refrigerate until ready to serve, then stir in club soda and ice. Garnish with fresh strawberries.
Serves

title: oakland inn pickled carrots
directions: Clean and peel carrots; cook in boiling water until done. Drain and slice.
Add rest of ingredients; mix and let marinate. The longer they marinate, the better.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and butter until fluffy; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg is added.
Sift flour first, then weigh;
add
flour
after
using
all the eggs.
Dust the fruit with 1/4 cup floured fruit last, small amount at a time, mixing well
after
each addition.
Bake in a tube pan or loaf pans at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
This recipe makes about 8 pounds of cooked fruit cake.

title: grandmere's maque choux
directions: Cut kernels from cob twice if small; 3 times if large, then slightly scrape cob.
Barely heat cooking oil in a 2-quart pot. Add onion and bell pepper and cook over low heat until onion is clear, 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add salt to corn; add corn to onion and bell pepper mixture.
Stir often to avoid scorching.
Cook until kernels are clear.
Add pepper and tomatoes.
Cover mixture when it starts to bubble around edges; reduce heat to low and cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tex mex bean dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Place in layers on large pizza pan or cookie sheet, starting with bean dip and continuing in order given above.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: quick enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions.
Add chili powder, salt and pepper to taste.
Spray Pam on 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle 2 to 3 tablespoons meat on tortilla.
Sprinkle cheese on tortilla.
Fold up.

title: european style peas and mushrooms
directions: In medium skillet, simmer undrained mushrooms, onion, oregano, garlic and wine for 3 minutes.
Stir in peas; heat thoroughly. Makes 4 servings.

title: impossible cheesecake pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inch).
Place milk, vanilla, eggs, sugar and baking mix into blender.
Blend on high 15 seconds.
Add cream cheese.
Blend on high 2 minutes. Pour into pie plate.
Bake until firm 40 to 45 minutes.
Spread cheesecake topping over top after cooling.

title: dessert salad
directions: Place cottage cheese in medium to large size bowl.
Add dry Jell-O directly from the box.
Add Cool Whip, fruit and nuts. Chill.
Good for a pot luck.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Break up cranberry sauce with a fork.
Stir into gelatin with cherry and nuts.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into an oiled 1-quart mold and chill until firm.

title: provencale pizzas
directions: Cut bread lengthwise; then cut crosswise 4 times, making 8 pieces.
Toast under broiler for about 1 or 2 minutes, until golden.
Preheat oven to 450°.

title: german apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla to the well beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture in small amounts to egg mixture.
Beat well by hand after each addition.
When all the flour mixture has been added, mix in the apples and nuts.
Mix well.

title: chewy licorice
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients to firm ball at 235°, stirring constantly.
Add flavoring and coloring.
Pour in dripper pan and cool.
Cut in square pieces and wrap in wax paper.

title: world's best gravy
directions: First remove nearly all fat from pan and then scrape drippings loose.
Depending on how much drippings you have and on how much gravy you need, start with 1 tablespoon of cornstarch in 1 cup cold water or veggie juice.
Shake in garlic powder to taste and add 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Stir or shake in a bottle.
Add to hot drippings and stir constantly.
Add wine, salt and pepper to taste.
This thickens rapidly so never leave it alone.

title: delicious cake
directions: Select your favorite cake mix. Spray pan(s) with cooking spray.
Prepare according to package directions with the following modifications.
Add 1 tablespoon flour to the dry mix and blend well.
Substitute an equal number of egg whites for whole eggs and substitute equal amount of applesauce for vegetable oil. Cool in pan. Remove when cool. Frost cake and garnish with fresh fruits.

title: key lime cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares while cake is warm. Leave cake in pan.
Combine powdered sugar and 1/4 cup lime juice. Pour over warm cake.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (in rectangular pan or Pyrex dish).

title: party potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes.
Beat in cream cheese, sour cream, butter and salt (garlic powder optional) until fluffy.
Sprinkle Cheddar and paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Bake longer if refrigerated.
Can be prepared in advance.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls out in bottom of cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.
Mix Ranch dressing according to directions.
Beat in cream cheese.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with cut up vegetables of choice.
Cool and cut in pieces to serve.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Put jelly, mustard and catsup in crock-pot on medium heat. When well blended and hot (30 to 45 minutes), add wieners that have been chopped in 1-inch pieces.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Roll graham crackers until real fine, then mix fruit, nuts, raisins and crumbs together. Put milk in pan on low heat and put marshmallows in and stir until it is real creamy. Pour it over the mixture and mix well. Dampen hands in water before mixing. Grease wax paper and line pan all over. Refrigerate overnight. Take out of pan next day and wrap up. Leave 1 month before cutting.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1 stick melted butter and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Stir the flour, milk, eggs and salt together until smooth. Blend in the cheese, a tablespoon at a time.
Grease a muffin tin with salad oil.
Fill each cup half full with batter.
Bake for 20 minutes at 450°.

title: hershey bar pudding
directions: Melt Hershey bars in microwave; add other ingredients.
Fold whipped cream or Cool Whip into mixture.
Line dish with whole vanilla wafers and pour pudding mixture over them.
Crush several vanilla wafers and sprinkle crumbs over top of pudding mixture.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix Kre-mel and sugar.
Add water and boil to 280° (hard-crack stage).
Remove from stove.
Add soda and peanuts and spread out in pan, lightly oiled with butter.
When cold, break in pieces.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar and milk together with mixer. Pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells.
Drain pineapple; spread it on top of cream cheese mixture.
Slice bananas on top of pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Put a few cherries and nuts on for decoration, if wanted.

title: elegant crock-pot chicken
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, water and spice together in crock-pot. Add whole or cubed chicken breasts.
Cook on low all day.
Serve over rice.
A salad, green beans and bread will complete the meal.

title: ham quiche
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and gently prick with a fork.
Bake 5 minutes longer. Let cool on rack.
Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk; mix thoroughly.
Stir in ham and cheese.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar and beat in egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Mix well.
Cool.
Form in small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Batter may be kept for days in covered bowl in refrigerator.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour with other dry ingredients.
Alternate with bananas to butter/sugar.
Mix in sour cream and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate bundt cake
directions: Mix by hand or beat on low if use mixer.
Bake for 1 hour at 300° in greased Bundt pan.
Let sit 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: red cinnamon grapefruit jelly
directions: Dissolve cinnamon candies in hot water. Add grapefruit juice and powdered pectin. Cook over high heat until mixture boils hard. Stir in sugar immediately. Let mixture come again to a rolling boil. Boil hard for 30 seconds. Remove from heat and add coloring. Pour into hot, clean jars and seal. Process in boiling water for 10 minutes. Yields 5 one-half pints.

title: english muffins
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Scald milk.
Add shortening, salt and sugar.
Cool.
Stir in yeast.
Add 1 beaten egg.
Stir in flour. Knead.
Let rise.
Roll out and cut in circles.
Let rise.
Bake slowly on a griddle about 7 minutes on each side.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and margarine; beat with electric mixer until fluffy.
Stir in pimiento, 1 tablespoon parsley and onion.
Chill.
Shape into a ball.
Coat with nuts and 1/3 cup parsley.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: cabbage rolls (chicken)
directions: Core and blanch cabbage to loosen leaves, yields about 8 large plus 8 medium size leaves.
Cook barley per package directions. Saute leeks in 1/2 of the margarine.
Skin and bone chicken; slice into strips.

title: egg and cheese casserole
directions: Combine eggs, flour and baking powder, stirring well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a lightly floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix ingredients, except marshmallows, and bake at 300 for 30-45 minutes.
Cover with small marshmallows right out of oven.

title: trish's monkey bread
directions: Well grease a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put pecans in bottom of pan.
"Stretch and twist" biscuits.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Layer in Bundt pan.
Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar.
Pour brown sugar-margarine mixture over biscuits.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: cheese spread
directions: Beat until smooth with mixer.

title: dilly beans
directions: Cook beans until tender; 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and place in jar.
To each jar add 1 clove of garlic and 1 head of dill.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture in jar and seal. Cold pack for about 20 minutes.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Soften cheese and work all ingredients together by hand.
Roll into marble size balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Rinse, pat dry and slice the mushrooms (makes about 5 cups). In a large saucepan, heat 4 tablespoons of the butter.
Add mushrooms and saute over high heat until lightly
browned.
Remove mushrooms; set aside.
In the same saucepan, heat the remaining tablespoon butter.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add broth.
Add onion, bay leaves, basil, salt and white pepper.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add milk.
Cook over low heat 8 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Do not boil.
Remove onion slice and bay leaves.
Return sauteed mushrooms to saucepan.
Heat.
Serve in warm bowls with crackers, if desired.
Yields 6 portions.

title: nice summer drink
directions: Heat water and sugar. Let cool.
Once cool,
mix with other ingredients and freeze.
Spoon into glasses frozen.
Add 7-Up or ginger ale.

title: chocolate carrot cake
directions: Sift together in a bowl the flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Beat in cooking oil and eggs, one at a time. Stir in carrots and cinnamon. Bake at 350° in 3 (8-inch) pans or 2 (9-inch) pans for 25 to 30 minutes. Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: sauerkraut in a jar
directions: Gather fresh cabbage (is best).
Shred as desired.
Pack, not too tight, into sterilized jars.
To each quart jar, add canning or clean stock salt.
Pour briskly over this boiling water.
With stainless steel knife, punch out air.
Quickly seal jars and set aside.
In a few days, it will spoil but don't bother it.
In about 18 to 21 days, it is ready to use or replace lids with new ones and hot water bath for 5 minutes.
Remove and it seals.
This will keep for a long time.

title: spinach dish
directions: Chop onion; drain spinach.
Cook bacon until brown, then set aside.
In bacon fat, cook onion until done.
Add spinach, let get hot, then add beaten egg (cooked).
Serve with corn bread.

title: seneca goulash
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and pour off grease. Remove beef from skillet. Season with salt and pepper.

title: no bake fruitcake
directions: Heat fruit juice in pan, over low heat.
Add marshmallows, stir until smooth.
Remove from heat and cool.
Crush graham crackers fine.
Mix crumbs, raisins, fruit and nuts.
Add to the marshmallow mixture and blend well.
Line pans with wax paper, pour in cake mixture, press down firmly.
Wet hands before pressing down cake. This will keep a long time if wrapped in wax paper.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: taco pie
directions: Prick
bottom and sides of pie crust with fork; bake 10 minutes
Reduce oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onions in skillet;
drain.
Add
taco
seasoning
by directions.
In bowl combine
beans
and 1/3 cup taco sauce; mix well.
Layer half
of bean mixture in crust; top with 1/2 of seasoned meat, 1
cup cheese and crushed chips.
Repeat (except chips).
Bake for
minutes.
Remove from oven. Top with lettuce, tomato and taco sauce, if desired.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Place burritos in a long glass baking dish that has been sprayed with a baking spray.
Top with chili and cheese and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 20 minutes and then top with sour cream and green onions.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix together and put into unbaked pie shell and lattice the top.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Decrease heat to 350° until done, about 20 more minutes.

title: nut caramels
directions: Stir sugar, syrup and milk together.
Add butter and start on low fire to cook.
Gradually increase heat as mixture starts cooking.
Cook until hard ball forms when dropped in cold water. This takes 1/2 to 1 hour.
Stir continuously.
Cooks down very thick.
Remove from fire, stir in nutmeats and spread on buttered tin.
Cut in small squares and wrap in waxed paper.

title: sinful cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg and butter.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts and put into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Beat cream cheese, 3 eggs, vanilla and powdered sugar until smooth.
Spread evenly over cake mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: egg biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl, make hole in middle, add wet ingredients and mix to soft dough.
Do not knead.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 425°.
Do not overcook.
May be frosted.

title: four-bean salad
directions: Drain liquid off beans; add onion.
Mix with sugar or honey, oil and lemon juice.
Season with salt.
Mix all together and let stand several hours or overnight, stirring several times.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil the eggplant in salt water with onion and green pepper. Mash and drain. Add egg and melted butter.
Layer eggplant mixture, cracker crumbs and cheese in casserole dish. Top with more cracker crumbs and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Saute carrots and onions in butter until tender. Add flour to make roux paste. Bring water to boil and add bouillon cubes. When dissolved, add roux to water. Whisk to smoothness. Add Cheez Whiz. When melted, add half and half and liquid smoke. Season to taste.

title: lettuce-cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and drain lettuce and cauliflower.
Chop and line bottom of large bowl with lettuce.
Add layer of chopped (bite-size) cauliflower.
Add layer of thinly sliced onion.
Crumble crisp bacon over onion.
Spread mayonnaise over all like icing. Sprinkle with sugar, then cheese.
Cover bowl and chill for 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Toss together before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and spices well.
Add zucchini.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown. Makes 3 loaves.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix in order given and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake
at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 40 minutes.

title: spicy turkey roast
directions: Remove mesh from the turkey.
Lay turkey out as flat as possible on cutting board, placing the skin side down.
Combine the garlic, rosemary, paprika, pepper and salt in blender or food processor.
Turn on; add oil and process until coarsely chopped. Spread half the garlic mixture over the inside of the turkey. Re-roll the turkey.
Tie firmly with string every 2-inches to return the meat to its original log shape.
Spread evenly with the remaining garlic mixture.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Roast at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until a meat thermometer inserted in the center registers 170°.
A long log shape takes less time than a more compact roast.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 20 minutes before removing string.
Cut thin slices to serve.
Scrape up cooking juices from bottom of pan.
Spoon over meat or thicken with flour and add chicken broth for a gravy, if desired.

title: ruth's chicken and rice "tostada"
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cut chicken into chunks.
In large pot, bring 3 cups water to boil; add chopped chicken, 1 cup uncooked rice, 1 onion (chopped), 4 cloves garlic (crushed) and pepper, if desired.
Cook (simmer) until rice is tender.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in 1 1/2 gallons water.
Dissolve Kool-Aid in 1 quart water.
Mix with juices and pour over crushed ice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and stir in ice cubes until melted and starts to thicken.
Set aside and let cool.
Mix cream cheese with a little pineapple juice.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Mix with jello and chill until firm. Delicious!!

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in large bowl in that order.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar together.
Spread on top of salad.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Top with boiled eggs and bacon.

title: chocolate butter creams(diabetic)
directions: Beat cream cheese, milk and vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in powdered sugar replacement.
Form into 30 balls and dip each one in chocolate.
Yields 30 creams.

title: butter brickle bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.	Bake for 15 minutes at 250° and 45 minutes at 300°.
Keep 1 loaf for your family and send one to a friend.

title: rebecca's pesto plus
directions: Prepare pasta, rinse in warm water, drain and toss with olive oil.
Prepare pasta sauce as instructed on package.
Add sliced mushrooms, according to your liking.
Heat crab 5 minutes in microwave.
Combine pesto sauce and crab and heat for 5 more minutes.
Toss with pasta.
Serve with Parmesan cheese and garlic bread.
Delizioso!

title: macaroni and sausage casserole
directions: Remove casing from sausage and brown in skillet.
Add celery and cook lightly.
Drain fat.
Add puree, basil and salt.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: one-pot chicken
directions: Saute chicken, onion and garlic in oil for 3 minutes until outside of chicken is not longer pink. Stir in water. Bring to boiling.
Stir in rice and pepperoni.
Lower heat. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is just tender but still firm. Add peas and pimento.
Cover and cook 5 minutes longer or until peas are heated through. Serves 4.

title: aloha cake
directions: Bake Jiffy cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan following directions on back of box.
Mix in bowl the cream cheese, pineapple, milk and pudding.
