After cake cools, spread the pudding mixture on top of cake.
Slice bananas on top, then spread Cool Whip over bananas. Put cherries on top.

title: summer pie
directions: Mix the yogurt and Cool Whip together.
Pour into pie shell. Decorate with strawberries.
Chill.

title: almond joy bars
directions: Melt butter.
Add condensed milk.
Mix.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture over sifted 10x sugar.
Add coconut and pecans.
Mix with mixer about 5 to 6 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Slice egg and place on top and sprinkle with paprika if desired.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice at least 1 inch thick enough sweet potatoes to fill a 3-quart saucepan very full.
Add water and boil potatoes a few minute, but do not overcook.
Potatoes should still be firm. Remove from water into a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch deep baking dish and arrange evenly in pan.
Sprinkle salt, cinnamon and butter over potatoes and add sugar and syrup evenly.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until syrup thickens.
Gently turn potatoes 2 to 3 times during baking process so all potatoes will candy evenly.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix the flour, sugar and salt; set aside. In medium saucepan, boil the oleo, cocoa and water for 1 minute. In a small bowl, mix well the eggs, buttermilk, vinegar, baking soda and vanilla.
Add moist mixture to dry ingredients in large bowl; mix well, then pour into a greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Frost cake while hot.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Repeat.
Top with hoop cheese and then with bacon bits.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add lemon extract.
Add flour and 7-Up alternately, beating well after each.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cabbage lemon salad
directions: Combine vegetables and pour oil over them.
Let stand while you heat vinegar, water, sugar, mustard seed, salt and celery seed.
When mixture boils, add jello and stir until dissolved. Cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Keeps for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: tyler's toast
directions: Toast bread in toaster.
Spread with peanut butter while hot. Sprinkle chocolate chips or raisins on top.
Serve with rice, sliced peaches or oatmeal.

title: slow cooker hearty beef and bean chile
directions: Cook beef in skillet until browned. Pour off fat. Mix beef, onion, garlic, soup, tomatoes, water, beans, chili powder and cumin in 3 1/2 qt. slow cooker. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, cooking oil and vinegar.
Sift cake flour and soda together.
Add flour to mixture.
Add milk slowly. Add flavoring and cake coloring.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 layers.

title: orange creme brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
With foil, line the bottom and sides of a 9-inch square baking pan, allowing foil to overhang slightly. Butter foil and set aside.
On a square of wax paper, combine flour, baking powder and salt.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook and crumble sausage.
Add onions and then drain.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix soups and milk.
Add meat, then noodles. Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: frank and kraut stew
directions: In large Dutch oven, cook green pepper and onion in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, kraut, carrots and potatoes.
Stir in 1 quart of water.
Add Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, salt and black pepper to taste.
Partially cover and simmer for 30 to 35 minutes, or until vegetables are nearly tender.
Add hot dogs; cover and cook 10 minutes more.
Serve with cornbread.
Delicious.

title: tahoe sunset cooler
directions: Fill with soda in chimney glass.

title: vegetable bars(appetizer - pot luck)
directions: Pat
the
rolls
to
fit in an 11 x 17-inch baking pan; bake at	350°
for 7 to 8 minutes, or until slightly browned. In a mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, cream cheese (softened)	and dressing mix; spread mixture over cooked crust in pan.
Mix
vegetables and cheese together well; distribute evenly over
cheese
mixture.
Cover with plastic; press down with hands, pushing vegetables into cheese mixture.
Refrigerate,
covered, for
to	4
hours.
Cut into bars to serve. Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: bizcochitos (anise-seed cookies)
directions: Cream lard, sugar and anise seed in a large mixing bowl. Add eggs and beat well.

title: hot sweet pickles
directions: Drain juice from dills. Add sugar.
Add garlic, Tabasco sauce and
more
Tabasco sauce if hotter pickles are desired. It	is hard to get the sugar in the jars.	Keep turning until all	sugar is in jars.
Let marinate five days, turning every day.

title: pineapple dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in 8 x 11-inch ungreased cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple.
Slice margarine evenly over cake mix.
Spread coconut and pecans over margarine.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream.
Quick and easy.

title: jello salad
directions: Pour boiling water over lime jello and marshmallows.
When dissolved, add pineapple.
Stir and cool until thick.
Fold in whipped cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix gently, but thoroughly. Pour into shallow pan 3 inches deep.
Allow to set.
Mix other 2 packages of jello with water and cool until thickish," then pour over lime mixture.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: crunchy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash according to package; drain well.
Saute onions in 1 tablespoon butter or oleo.
Combine squash, onions, sour cream, soup and water chestnuts.
Combine stuffing mix and remaining butter; stir well.
Add 3/4 of stuffing mixture to squash mixture; spoon into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop hearts.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, beat cheese until smooth.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.

title: gramma french dressing
directions: Mix in blender. Keep refrigerated. Shake before serving.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Thoroughly blend together cream cheese and Cheddar cheese. Fold in pineapple, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Refrigerate several hours.
Shape into ball and roll in nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.
(I divide it into 3 balls.)

title: baked rice
directions: Melt oleo in 2-quart baking dish.
Add rice, garlic salt, both soups and 2 soup cans filled with water.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hank's cajun red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight or quick soak.
Cook ham hocks in 3 cups boiling water at least 2 hours.
Drain beans.
Add all ingredients to hocks.
Continue to cook until ham hocks are tender, 30 minutes.
Remove ham hocks and cut into small pieces after it cools.
Slice sausage into 1/2-inch pieces and brown in skillet. Add sausage and ham to pot and cook another 30 to 40 minutes. Remove bay leaves and serve with rice.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, oil, water, pudding and eggs. After completely combined add chocolate chips and grated chocolate. Bake in greased and floured bundt pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minute.

title: molasses beans
directions: Combine all ingredients together in baking dish and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Wash rice carefully and place in large saucepan with water and salt.
Cover and cook over low heat for 5 minutes after boiling point is reached.
Drain and rinse with cold water twice.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Cut in shortening and add potatoes. Add enough milk to make dough stiff enough to roll. Cut with floured glass and place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes. Yields 12 biscuits.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until needed. Good sauce for just about anything.
Makes 2 cups.

title: spiced glazed nuts
directions: Mix egg white and water. Stir. Do not beat. Set aside. Mix all dry ingredients in a separate dish. Coat pecans in egg white mixture, then coat pecans in dry mixture. Bake 20 minutes at 250° on nonstick cookie sheet.

title: venison pot roast
directions: About 4 hours before serving, trim away excess fat.
On waxed paper, coat meat with flour.
In an 8-quart Dutch oven, over medium heat, in hot shortening, cook meat until brown on both sides.
Add 1 cup water, onion, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 3 hours, or until fork-tender, adding water, if needed.
About 45 minutes before meat is done, add carrots, potatoes and beans; sprinkle vegetables with 1 teaspoon salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce and cook until meat and vegetables are tender, stirring vegetables occasionally.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: holy chicken
directions: Salt chicken and cook until tender.
2 ribs of celery cooked with chicken.
Cut chicken into chunks, place chicken in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2 casserole.
Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream, and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Top with 1 large pkg. Ritz crackers (about 36) crushed fine.
Mix with 1 stick melted butter.
Sprinkle top heavily with poppy seed. Bake at 350° until brown and hot throughout.

title: cheese spread
directions: Use a blender to chop the vegetables.
Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix softened roll of sausage, flour and grated cheese in a bowl.
Form 1-inch balls; place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Remove cheese balls from oven; allow them to cool before placing them on plate.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugar, mix in potatoes, add eggs.
Add flour alternately with yeast liquid.
Let rise once, then refrigerate overnight.
Make out 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: texas pralines
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; cook together until the syrup forms a soft ball stage when tested in cold water (220°).
Remove from stove.
Add pecans, vanilla and butter.
Beat until mixture begins to hold shape.
Drop the candy from a spoon onto wax paper. Wrap in foil and store in a tightly covered container.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread oil evenly in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix beaten eggs, salt, chopped meat and grated cheese and set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Add milk to sifted flour slowly; batter should be thin.
Add dash of salt and mix well.
Pour into an oiled pan and spread evenly.
Spoon egg mixture evenly onto batter.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: elegant squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Steam squash until tender; 8 minutes. Drain in colander, mash with back of spoon to squeeze out excess liquid.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in large saucepan over medium heat. Stir in flour and cook 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boil and cook stirring 1 minute.
Add salt, pepper and nutmeg. Remove from heat.
Add squash, sour cream, pimientos, carrots and onions.
Melt remaining 1/4 cup butter, add stuffing and toss. Spread half the stuffing in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon on squash mixture and sprinkle with remaining stuffing.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly and hot.
Makes 12 servings.
Has 235 calories, 5 gm. protein, 13 gm. fat, 25 gm. carbohydrates, 564 mg. sodium, 32 mg. cholesterol.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir ground beef and onion in butter until brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms. Then cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Stir in soup. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: fish balls
directions: Drain fish, flakes and combine with other ingredients through salt.
Shape into 12 balls, using about 3 tablespoons for each. Roll in crumbs.
Place balls on lightly greased shallow baking pan. Bake in 350° oven about 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve dill sauce over balls.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese and margarine in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add powdered sugar and beat well.
Melt chocolate and beat into mixture.
Now, divide mixture in half.
Reserve 1/2 for icing. To the other half, add shortening and eggs.
Beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
If too thick, add 1/4 cup water.
Add vanilla last.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Ice cake when cool.

title: hot rolls
directions: Let rise twice, then roll out.
Makes two big cake pans full.

title: frozen bread pull-aparts
directions: Cut up frozen bread.
Place cut up bread into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Combine all other ingredients and put on top of bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: shredded potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets, peel.
Shred into buttered 4 quart casserole.
Melt cheese in milk with cream, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake one hour at 350 degrees.

title: brown sugar tapioca
directions: In a saucepan, combine tapioca, brown sugar , salt and water. Bring to a boil and stir until tapioca appears clear.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip.

title: graham-streusel coffee cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine cake mix, water, cooking oil and eggs. Beat on low speed until moistened.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour half of the batter into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with half the streusel mixture.
Carefully spread the remaining batter over the streusel; sprinkle with remaining streusel.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool slightly; drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.
Best served warm.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into a ball. Refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Toss together zucchini, lemon juice and salt. Mix rest of ingredients in bowl. Add zucchini and mix well. It will be runny, but that's OK. Dump filling into 9-inch crust and dot with butter. Add top crust and bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl. Serve over ice.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Heat oil and butter in wide frying pan over medium heat.
Add garlic and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in cream and clams.
Heat, but do not boil.
Meanwhile, cook linguini; drain well.
Put in serving bowl and pour clam mixture over it.
Stir in parsley and cheese. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pineapple chess pie with pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crispy peppers
directions: Mix vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Wash and cut green peppers in strips.
Fill jars; add garlic.
Pour liquid over peppers; add 1 tablespoon oil in each jar.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: caponata
directions: Day before serving:
In colander, toss eggplant with salt; place over bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and weight down.
Drain 1 hour, not dry.

title: baked lasagne
directions: Bring water and salt to a rolling boil in a large pot.
Add lasagne noodles and cook until just tender; do not overcook. Remove from heat and run cold water into pot until noodles are cold; then drain.

title: frozen angel food strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water and cool.
Drain frozen strawberries.
Soften ice cream.
Break cake into small chunks. Mix all together and put in tube pan.
Keep in freezer.

title: country chicken salad *
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Garnish with olives, if desired.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook grits in boiling, salted water until done (about 25 to 30 minutes).
Add Cheddar cheese, garlic cheese and margarine and stir until melted.
Beat eggs with milk. Add Tabasco and salt; mix together with grits mixture.
Pour into a well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: citrus beet soup
directions: Combine the onion, beets and orange juice in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 8 to 12 minutes or until the beets are tender, stirring once or twice.
Add the lemon juice, broth, cucumber and pepper.
Cover again and cook on High for 3 to 5 minutes, or until heated through, but not boiling.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip; stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon into crust.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Refrigerate.
Very good on beef, chicken or pork.

title: haystacks
directions: Mix well and drop on waxed paper by teaspoon.
Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix together to make a stiff dough.
Make a ball about 3-inches in diameter and pull the ball into a 6-inch circle with the fingers.
Do not use a rolling pin.
Heat 1-inch cooking oil in a skillet and when hot, drop in the bread round.
Brown on each side and drain.
Serve hot.

title: italian green beans
directions: The Thanksgiving feast has the tradition of being a shared meal.
When they gathered together to celebrate the harvest, the Indians and Pilgrims brought with them gifts from nature's bounty, pumpkins, squash, fowl and berries.
This started a warm tradition for a uniquely American holiday.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine all ingredients (except the extra cup of Longhorn cheese).
Spoon some in a tortilla shell.
Wrap up.
Continue until out of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with 1 cup cheese and bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 5 servings.

title: eagle brand milk
directions: Mix well together.
Can be used immediately.
Equal to 1 can Eagle Brand milk.

title: good-n-easy chicken
directions: Take chicken pieces, salt and pepper.
Put in a casserole dish.
Pour Italian dressing over chicken.
Cover with lid.
Cook until done at 375°.

title: meat loaf with vegetables
directions: Pour sauce over top of meat loaf and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Meanwhile, cook a few potatoes, carrots and onion.
Add to meat loaf last 5 minutes of cooking, spooning sauce over vegetables. Serve with cornbread.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Bring to boil vinegar, sugar, Crisco, celery seed, mustard and salt.
Pour sauce over vegetables.
Mix.
Chill for 8 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar well.
Add peanut butter. Blend.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill.
Serve.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush wafers.
Add all other ingredients.
Pack in container (loaf pan or other dish).
Chill in refrigerator for 1 day.

title: crumb torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and mix well. Spread half the crushed wafers on bottom of buttered 8-inch square pan, then butter mixture, then pineapple.
Add nuts to whipped cream and top with remaining crumbs.
Chill 2 hours.

title: brownie pie
directions: Sprinkle egg whites with salt and whip to soft peaks. Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in wafer crumbs, nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly in 9-inch buttered pie pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Spread with sweetened whipped cream.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: coffee punch
directions: Mix sugar, coffee, vanilla, milk and Kahlua.
Refrigerate. When ready to serve, scoop vanilla ice cream into punch bowl. Pour chilled mixture on top.

title: uncooked peanut butter cookies
directions: Boil for 1 minute the sugar, butter, cocoa and milk.
Remove from flame.
Pour over graham crackers, oats and peanut butter. Stir until mixed only.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Makes 2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients over medium heat for 4 minutes, stirring well.
Remove from heat and add last three ingredients. Blend well.
Drop by tablespoonful onto wax paper.
Cool and enjoy.

title: cinnamon pull-aparts
directions: In Bundt pan, spray Pam, place in rolls.
Sprinkle dry butterscotch pudding over rolls and cinnamon to taste.
In small pan, melt margarine and brown sugar; stir.
When melted, drizzle over rolls.
Cover with wax paper and let rise on counter overnight.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine avocados, onion, vinegar, salt, pepper and green chilies.
Beat until smooth on medium mixer speed.
Add finely chopped tomato and fold into mixture.
Serve with corn chips.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts; mix until well blended. Spoon mixture into 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve on crackers.

title: r c cola hostess ham
directions: Wash jelly off ham and place in crock-pot.
Pour cola over ham and cook on medium heat for 3 hours.
The cola gives the ham a smoked taste.

title: meatless tomato sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan, stirring until well blended.
Bring tomato mixture to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: turtles
directions: In saucepan, melt caramels and add milk.
Stir well.
Add nuts.
Spoon onto wax paper and let sit until firm.
Freeze.
Melt almond bark in double boiler.
Dip candy into bark and place on wax paper until set.
Store in tight container.

title: ground turkey stroganoff
directions: Brown ground turkey in 1 1/2 tablespoon Italian dressing. Crush up to keep pieces small.
When done, drain and stir in A.1. sauce.
Cook noodles; drain but do not rinse.
Prepare frozen broccoli and add onions and carrots to cook along with it as per directions on box.
Drain.
Heat both gravies in medium saucepan. Add onion salt, garlic salt, mushrooms and Worcestershire sauce to heated gravy and simmer one minute.
Add browned meat to gravy mix. Place noodles on plates.
Spoon on gravy mix and mix in.
Sprinkle drained vegetable mix over top or around sides to circle stroganoff.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 portions.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add Cheez Whiz, soup, rice and onions.
Stir well.
Add broccoli. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
If you're having company, double this recipe.

title: pina colada pancakes
directions: Mix Bisquick, eggs, Coco Lopez, vanilla (Kahlua) and enough milk to make a firm consistency.
Cook pancakes.

title: tropical banana split
directions: Mix milk with pudding mix until smooth, but not thick. Fold in the Cool Whip and sour cream, mixing well. Line large bowl with vanilla wafers. Slice layer of bananas; spread with some of the pudding mix. Spread half of pineapple mix, then layer of pudding mix. Next layer vanilla wafers, then bananas, then pudding mix. Spread other half of pineapple and more pudding mix. Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mix. This will make a large bowl of pudding. Sprinkle crushed wafers on top of pudding.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, oil and strawberries. Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour into 2 large greased and floured loaf pans or 4 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: molded asparagus salad
directions: Bring to boil sugar, water, vinegar and salt.
Dissolve 2 packages gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix this with remaining ingredients.
Mold.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla together.
Add flour and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto a greased pan.
Cook at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: caramelicious fudge brownies
directions: Prepare and bake brownie mix according to package directions. Meanwhile, in a small saucepan over low heat, melt caramels and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Immediately after removing brownies from oven, sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Drizzle with caramel.
Cool completely before cutting.
Makes 24 bars.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Mix the last 3 ingredients together and pour over chicken. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with hot buttered rice.

title: summer punch
directions: Squeeze the juice of lemons, grapefruit and lime into a gallon pitcher or jar.
Add sugar and flavorings.
Add water.

title: soft ginger drop cookies
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, then the water.
Stir until smooth.
Drop by teaspoon on to a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate hot oven at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost while still warm with Lemon Butter Icing.

title: oven rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish, stirring well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until liquid is absorbed.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add the strawberries (don't thaw, just stir in).
Add drained pineapple and chill.

title: apple-cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Set aside.
Mix together 1/2 cup butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix batter while gradually adding milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in apples.
Set aside.

title: red heart candy pickles
directions: Mix lime and enough water to cover the cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain and rinse in cold water until clear.
Drain.
Mix food coloring, white vinegar and water to cover cucumbers.
Simmer 2 hours.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients.
Bring to boil, pour over pickles and let stand 3 days, stirring occasionally.
Put in kettle and bring to boil.
Pack in hot jars.

title: chunky mexican dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with chips.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together except bacon and place in 3-quart casserole dish, then cut bacon into 1-inch pieces and place on top and sprinkle bacon with white sugar.
Bake in 350° oven 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crown jewel salad
directions: Congeal lime, cherry and orange jello in different pans, using only 1 1/2 cups of warm water for each.
Let congeal overnight. Boil sugar in 1 cup water, stir in lemon jello and add pineapple juice.
Chill until syrupy.
Whip cream cheese until smooth and fold in Cool Whip.
Cut congealed jello into small cubes.
Fold together cubed jello, cream cheese and Cool Whip and the syrupy jello.
Add pecans and let chill overnight.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chopped onion. Crumble on fried bacon.
Add diced cheese.
Add mayonnaise.
Stir. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Mix well the sour cream, taco mix and mayonnaise.
Spread over first two ingredients.
Mash avocados with lemon juice and spread over layers.
Add tomatoes, lettuce and olives, chopped.
Sprinkle over other ingredients.
Spread Cheddar cheese over this.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Butter large casserole and put in layer of Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Cover with layer of chicken, then broccoli.
Add soup and mushrooms with juice.
Cover with rest of dressing and a layer of almonds and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss style green beans
directions: Drain green beans and arrange half in bottom of a greased 2-quart baking dish. Beat eggs.

Blend in salt, pepper, tarragon and onion. Add cheeses to mixture. Spoon half of mixture over green beans. Add remaining green beans. Spread remaining mixture on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until cheese is melted and browned on top.

title: roasted wild goose or duck
directions: Clean & skin the bird as soon as possible.
Soak in saltwater for 45 minutes.

When ready to cook, soak bird in buttermilk overnight or for 4 - 6 hrs. (The easiest way is to place the bird in a plastic bag, set the bag in a pan, and pour in the buttermilk until the bird is covered.
After soaking, rinse thoroughly with cold water.
Stuff with cored and quartered apples, unpeeled. Place in roaster and cover breast with strips of bacon held in place with toothpicks.
Cook in covered roaster as follows:
500° for 30 minutes; 350° for remaining time. (20 min. per lb.)

title: mom's apple betty
directions: Put a layer of crumbled cornbread in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish (omit crust if hard).
Put a layer of apples over top of crumbs, then a layer of raisins over the top of the apples.
Repeat the procedure until all is used up.
You will have about 3 layers.
Put dabs of butter all over the top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add about 4 tablespoons of water.
Cover.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Take out and put in serving dishes and pour milk and sugar over the top.
Delicious.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all in crock-pot on low overnight or bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy enchiladas
directions: Brown beef; mix soup and sauce in bowl.
Dip shells in sauce mixture.
Fill with ground beef and cheese.
Roll and place in baking dish.
Continue until ingredients are gone.
Pour remaining sauce over top.
Add cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain off grease.
Pressure pinto beans for 30 minutes and drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook in slow pot overnight.
Bring to a boil and turn down on low.

title: mediterranean pasta salad
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, bring 3 cups water to boiling.
Add pasta; return to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Boil, uncovered, for 6 minutes.
Add carrot strips; cook for 2 to 4 minutes more or until pasta is tender but slightly firm and carrot strips are crisp-tender.
Drain pasta and carrot strips; rinse with cold water.
Drain again.

title: pecan praline pie(absolutely delicious - and too easy for words)
directions: Prepare pudding.
Set aside 1 cup of prepared pudding.
When pecan mixture is cool, pour pudding over it.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip and the reserved 1 cup of pudding.
Garnish with pecans.

title: grammy's stuffing
directions: Cut up onions and celery.
Melt 1/2 of butter in pan.
Place onions and celery in pan.
Sprinkle all seasonings on top.
Add the other 1/2 of butter. Cook slowly with lid on pan.
Cook until onions are clear.
Let cool.
Toast loaf of bread. Cut or break into bite sized pieces.
Add onion mixture to bread.
Mix well. Add a little bit of milk to moisten if necessary.
May be put into turkey or oven stuffer roaster.

title: "miss" lonnie mae's ground beef casserole
directions: Saute onions and bell peppers, add ground beef and stir until beef is browned.
Drain.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, tomatoes, cheese and sour cream together.
Add meat mixture and macaroni to this.
Pour in casserole dish and bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and top with fried onion rings and bake for another 10 minutes.

title: tina's sausage jambalaya
directions: Fry sausage until darkened.
Put onion and seasoning in pot with sausage; you may add a little water, if needed.
When sausage and onion are fried, put 1 cup rice and 2 cups water.
When water starts to boil, lower heat and cover for about 20 minutes.

title: irish soda bread(makes 1 large round loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put all dry ingredients in a large bowl and stir well.
Add raisins and stir.
Then add egg and oil. Gradually add buttermilk until you have a firm, but not stiff, dough, like biscuit dough.

title: cake donuts
directions: Gradually add sugar to eggs, beating well after each addition. Beat in shortening.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine milk and flavoring.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture alternately with milk mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Chill dough.
Turn out on floured pastry cloth and knead 3 to 4 times to form ball.
Cut in half.
Roll each half 1/3 inch thick.
Cut donuts.
Allow to stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Fry in deep fat.
Makes approximately 30 donuts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix well. Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture, mixing well.
Add nuts and raisins or dates.
Bake in greased pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Mix water, eggs, shortening, salt and sugar.
Add yeast mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Let rise once and punch down. Knead very little and form into rolls or loaves.
Bake at 425° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa, and oleo in pan. Bring to a boil. Cook 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add oats, vanilla, peanut butter, and coconut. Drop by teaspoons on wax paper. Nuts may be added, if desired.

title: chocolate chip cheese delight
directions: Take 1 package of cookie mix and slice thin on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, vanilla and sugar. Spread this mixture over cookie slices in pan.
Slice other package of cookie mix over cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes.
Check while baking as oven temperatures vary.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix brown sugar and milk.
Stir until the sugar is dissolved, then boil without stirring to the soft-ball stage (238° on candy thermometer).
Add butter.
Remove the icing until it is thick and creamy.
If the icing becomes too thick, thin it with a little cream.
Makes enough to frost 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix first layer ingredients together and put into a 9 X 13 dish.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 370 degrees.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate swirl divinity
directions: In heavy 2-quart saucepan, stir together sugar, corn syrup, water and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.

Cook without stirring until temperature on candy thermometer reaches 250° or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a ball which is hard enough to hold its shape, yet elastic.
Remove from heat.

title: nebraska plain pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in shell and bake until brown.
You can use whipped cream on top.
Bake at 350°.

title: cream cheese snowcaps
directions: Combine flour and baking powder.
In a small mixer bowl beat butter or margarine and cream cheese till softened and well blended.
Add sugar and extract and beat until fluffy.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Cover and chill for 1 to 2 hours or until easy to handle.

title: sweetheart corn bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sour cream, oil and corn; mix well.
Stir in corn meal just until combined.
Pour into a greased and floured heart shaped pan or a 9-inch round pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: chicken bette
directions: Place dry, uncooked rice in a 9 x 13-inch pan, or larger if recipe is doubled.
Break up bouillon cubes or granules over dry rice.
Place dry onion soup, green pepper and mushrooms over dry rice.
Cover with cold water.
Place uncooked chicken breasts over top of all ingredients.
Cover with soup concentrate in globs. Top with sliced almonds. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: clam and corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, saute celery and onion in margarine; stir in water, shell macaroni, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes or until the macaroni is tender.
Stir in milk, corn and clams.
Cook just until heated.

title: pie crust for 8 or 9-inch(2 crust)
directions: Blend shortening, salt and flour with pastry blender in a medium size bowl.
Mixture will resemble coarse crumbs when ready. Gradually sprinkle cold water, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Toss the mixture lightly with fork after each addition.
To roll, place between waxed paper.
For cream pies, prick single crust; bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: saucy burritos
directions: Cook ground beef, drain, add Ro-Tel and taco seasoning (do not add water to mix).
Simmer.
Prepare refried beans.
Grate lettuce and dice tomatoes, set aside.
Mix 1 cup sour cream with 1/2 cup salsa.
Set aside.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine sugars and half and half; cook over medium heat at a rolling boil, stirring constantly for 6 to 7 minutes.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla.
Stir until margarine melts, then set pan in ice water; stir until icing is of consistency to spread on cooled cake.
If too thick, add a few drops of milk.

title: cajun french cabbage rolls
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onions, celery and garlic and cook until wilted.
Remove 12 outer leaves from cabbage; parboil these for 15 minutes.
Drain and set aside; cut up center of cabbage (not the core) to equal 1 cup.
Cook until tender and add to meat mixture with 1 teaspoon tomato paste.
Add rice; mix and stuff cabbage leaves.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: taco pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add taco seasoning and spread on good size platter.
Top with shredded lettuce, grated cheese, black and green olives, tomatoes and onions.
Serve with nacho or Doritos chips.

title: bionic bars
directions: In blender, combine first 6 ingredients (kidney beans, oil, egg, honey, molasses and applesauce).
In large bowl, mix dry ingredients (flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, cloves, allspice and nutmeg).
Stir liquid mixture into dry ingredients.
Fold in chocolate chips and raisins.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; cut into 24 bars. Great for camping, hiking and skiing trips.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain the beans and mix all ingredients together.
Let this marinate at least 24 hours.
Serves approximately 10 to 12.

title: special cole slaw
directions: In small saucepan, combine honey with vinegar and salt.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Cool.
Pour dressing over prepared vegetables and toss.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.

title: keema mattar(ground meat with fresh peas)
directions: Heat butter and fry onion until soft. Add garlic and ginger. Fry until onion is golden. Add turmeric and chili powder, stirring for a few seconds.
Add meat, frying until meat changes color. Stir in yogurt and peas. Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Add garam masala and continue cooking until meat and peas are tender.

title: taco popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in roasting pan; drizzle with margarine.
Stir together taco seasoning and brown sugar; sprinkle over popcorn. Toss until combined.
Bake at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: homemade ketchup(noncook)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a squeeze bottle and shake well. Store in refrigerator.

title: shrimp pasta dijonnaise
directions: In large skillet heat corn oil over medium high heat.
Add shrimp and garlic; saute 2 minutes or until pink.
Remove from heat.
Stir in wine, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
In large bowl, combine shrimp, pasta, artichokes, peppers, olives and green onions.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip, pineapple and nuts.
Add Jell-O; mix well.
Add nuts or fruit on top if desired. Refrigerate.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, raisins, bacon and onion in bowl.
In separate container mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over broccoli mix.
Chill one hour.

title: old fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add egg.
Mix dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk and molasses.

title: creamy corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs.
Blend together cornstarch and sugar.
Combine with eggs.
Add this to the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Place dish in a pan of water.
Bake for about 50 minutes or until custard is set.

title: bread pudding
directions: Add sugar, salt and vanilla to hot milk.
Cool a little, then add to eggs which have been beaten until light and fluffy.
Put bread into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with raisins, then pour the milk and egg mixture over it.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Pour in hot brown sugar mix, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick and pour in baked crust.

title: mint chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
When well blended, stir in chips.
Bake in 15 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: posole
directions: *Posole found in frozen food section.

title: cheese and cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook whole heads of cauliflower in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain and cut into small pieces.
Arrange in a buttered casserole dish.
Cream together remaining ingredients and pour over cauliflower.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fat free ranch spinach dip
directions: Mix dip mix and sour cream together until well blended.
Add thawed spinach and chopped water chestnuts.
Mix together and serve.
Can be put in center of bread bowl, if desired.

title: cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg, margarine and pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs thoroughly.
Pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes (350° for 35 to 40 minutes, if using a glass baking dish).
Let stand to cool, then cut into bars.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: apple bundt cake
directions: Combine.
Bake one hour at 325° or until done.

title: front porch lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and boiling water.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add lemon juice and cold water.
Mix well.
Chill and serve over ice.

title: swiss egg pie
directions: Beat last 4 ingredients well together.
Pour over cheese. Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes, then turn oven to 325° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: jalapeno hot rice
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion, green pepper and jalapenos in butter until tender.
Add the rice, mushrooms and the chicken broth; cover and simmer until the rice is tender.

title: microwave spicy pecans
directions: Place butter and seasonings in a 3-quart casserole dish. Microwave for 1 minute.
Add pecan halves and stir until coated. Microwave another 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir several times during cooking.
Drain off any excess butter.
Spread pecans out onto paper towel to absorb excess butter.
Stores well in an airtight container.
